"0013║$atar_exp_010p0" = "Lightning and Sazh are held aboard a military 'Purge' train along with a group of civilians destined for exile. In stark contrast to the uncertain and despairing people around her, Lightning appears determined and focused.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}She seizes upon an instant of inattention to disable a guard, and her impressive display inspires Sazh and the other civilians to take up arms against the soldiers.{Text NewLine}{Text 112}After clashing with army forces, the train crashes to a halt in the war-torn district known as the Hanging Edge.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Sazh attempts to figure out Lightning's angle, but she shows little desire to share. The former soldier throws herself into battle without the slightest hint of hesitation{Var85 87}what could be driving her...?";
"0014║$atar_exp_020p0" = "Suspect citizens of Cocoon are wrenched from their tranquil existence and threatened with exile to the world of Pulse. The Purge has begun.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}The 'land below' is said to crawl with unknown perils, and terrified civilians begin to rebel against the Purge. A revolt also occurs on the train transporting Purge deportees, as Lightning's battle against the guards galvanizes the other prisoners into action.{Text NewLine}{Text 112}The train comes to a halt in the district of the Hanging Edge{Var85 87}now a hellish war zone where soldiers open fire indiscriminately upon civilians.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Lightning makes her way through the middle of the conflict, all but ignoring her uninvited companion, Sazh. She seems determined to press onwards even when the path before her is destroyed by military strikes.";
"0015║$atar_exp_030p0" = "The peaceful citizens of Cocoon live in constant fear of invasion by the forces of Pulse{Var85 87}the world below and supposed home of terrors unknown.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Were even a single Pulsian agent to be discovered on Cocoon, panic and civil unrest would be sure to follow, threatening the very fabric of society. To prevent such a calamity, the Sanctum (Cocoon's governing body) initiates the 'Purge'{Var85 87}a government initiative officially entailing the deportation of all those who may have come into contact with corrupting Pulsian influences.";
"0016║$atar_exp_030p1" = "However, the Sanctum army is now brutally slaughtering the civilians they were supposed to be deporting.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Realizing that the Purge is nothing more than a massacre in disguise, Snow leads the young freedom fighters of NORA in an effort to protect the Purge 'deportees' from the Sanctum soldiers.";
"0017║$atar_exp_040p0" = "The Purge is a Sanctum initiative designed to protect the stability of Cocoon by forcing potentially dangerous civilians to relocate to Pulse.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}However, the relocation is simply a facade to cover the massacre that ensues. The government's true goal is the brutal extermination of all possible threats to a peaceful society.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Having discovered the horrific truth, Snow leads the members of NORA against the government soldiers of PSICOM.";
"0018║$atar_exp_040p1" = "Inspired by the actions of this handful of brave young men and women, the beleaguered civilians take heart and join the battle in hope of returning to a normal life.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Among the citizens who stand against the forces of PSICOM is a mother who wishes for nothing more than to protect her son.";
"0019║$atar_exp_050p0" = "Cocoon's citizens have always been terrified of Pulse and the mysterious horrors that are said to stalk its hostile wastelands.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Their fear is so great that if a Cocoon native were to have even the briefest contact with Pulsian elements, former friends and neighbors would consider them corrupted and dangerous.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}In light of this fact, the Sanctum orders the Purging of Bodhum in an effort to remove all potentially Pulse-tainted civilians.";
"0020║$atar_exp_050p1" = "Accordingly, soldiers round up all those identified as candidates for relocation and inform them of their impending exile.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}However, PSICOM, the elite arm of the Sanctum military, then begins to massacre the helpless civilians. This prompts Snow to lead the people in a rebellion against the army. Tragically, one of the civilians who decides to follow him, hoping to protect her son, dies in the act of saving Snow's life.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}From afar, the boy witnesses the moment of his mother's death in shock and disbelief.";
"0021║$atar_exp_060p0" = "A massive object is transported through the sky over the Hanging Edge. This object is a Pulse Vestige{Var85 87}a lowerworld artifact that had been nothing more than a Bodhum landmark. Two days ago, it was discovered that the Vestige housed a long dormant Pulse fal'Cie.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}The fal'Cie had slumbered undisturbed on the outskirts of a Cocoon city for centuries. The Sanctum decrees that the presence of the Pulse entity and its corrupting magics have tainted the entire population of the city, and orders the Purge.";
"0022║$atar_exp_060p1" = "For different reasons, Lightning and Sazh now make their way towards the very being that was the catalyst for so much tragedy.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Snow, meanwhile, is crushed by feelings of guilt after many die under his command. He only emerges from his gloom when Gadot reminds him that the fal'Cie is holding a certain young lady captive{Var85 87}who needs her hero now more than ever.";
"0023║$atar_exp_070p0" = "Snow still cannot shake his feelings of guilt. Despite his efforts to protect the Purge deportees from the Sanctum forces, many have fallen.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}The death of one woman in particular haunts his thoughts: a mother fighting for the sake of her son, who gave her life to save Snow.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}In the moments before her death, the woman begged the leader of NORA to take care of her child, but slipped from Snow's grasp without revealing the boy's identity.";
"0024║$atar_exp_070p1" = "With Gadot's help, Snow breaks out of his depression. He figures that if he just goes ahead and protects everyone, then the woman's son will be saved as well.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}After checking to see if the children are safe, Snow leaves the waning battle to his fellow NORA members and sets off with new determination towards the Vestige. His fianc{Var85 200}e is still held captive by the Pulse fal'Cie.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}A boy watches him leave, eyes filled with rage and loathing. To his grief-stricken mind, Snow is responsible for his mother's death.";
"0025║$atar_exp_080p0" = "For centuries, a Pulse fal'Cie has slumbered undisturbed on the outskirts of a Cocoon city. On the day the lowerworld entity is finally discovered, Cocoon's peaceful society is plunged into chaos.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}The government judges the city's inhabitants to have been tainted by their unwelcome guest, and begins a merciless campaign to expunge both the fal'Cie and the 'corrupted' citizenry from the face of Cocoon.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Instead of the exile they were led to expect, the civilians face extermination at the hands of the Sanctum army.";
"0026║$atar_exp_080p1" = "The people attempt to fight back, but are hopelessly outmatched by the military.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Lightning cuts her way through this battlefield, doggedly followed by the desperate Sazh.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Snow, meanwhile, seeks to rescue his fianc{Var85 200}e.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}...And a boy spurred on by dreams of revenge pursues Snow with the help of an unusual young lady.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Though driven by separate goals, their paths all lead to the same end: the Pulse fal'Cie.";
"0027║$atar_exp_090p0" = "Hope has fallen into a panic.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}In his single-minded pursuit of Snow, he has rushed into the lair of a fal'Cie and is only now recalling the terrible nature of the being that lurks within. The Pulse entity could use its power to curse them{Var85 87}to turn them into l'Cie.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Pulse l'Cie are the doomed servants of the fal'Cie who created them, despised and feared by the people of Cocoon.";
"0028║$atar_exp_090p1" = "Hope's companion, Vanille, seems unconcerned by this dreadful possibility. Bemused by her indomitable cheerfulness, he nervously follows her in search of Snow.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}It was Snow who convinced his mother to fight. It was Snow she was protecting when she died. And it is Snow who must be made to pay.";
"0029║$atar_exp_100p0" = "To the citizens of Cocoon, the lowerworld of Pulse is a hell rife with unknown terrors, and the recently discovered Pulse fal'Cie is an invader from that hell.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}In an effort to quell the growing panic in the wake of the entity's discovery, the Sanctum initiates an extreme measure known as the Purge. Under this initiative, not only is the fal'Cie to be cast out of Cocoon, but all of the civilians living nearby as well.";
"0030║$atar_exp_100p1" = "Any person coming into contact with the lowerworld being's foul energies could already be corrupted, and no potential enemies of Cocoon can be allowed to remain.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}The ensuing 'deportation' claims the lives of countless civilians, Hope's mother among them. After witnessing her death and chasing Snow into the Vestige in a blind rage, Hope suddenly realizes that he may soon share the same fate as the Pulse fal'Cie: relocation to the world below.{Text NewLine}{Text 112}Vanille, however, calmly accepts the situation, and lends her support to the distraught boy.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Unaware of his young pursuers, Snow begins exploring the arcane halls and chambers of the shrine-like Vestige in search of his captive fianc{Var85 200}e, Serah.";
"0031║$atar_exp_110p0" = "The Pulse fal'Cie{Var85 87}an entity that threatens the peace of Cocoon's society{Var85 87}holds Snow's fianc{Var85 200}e captive.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}As the determined Snow delves ever deeper into the alien structure, Lightning and Sazh arrive at the Vestige after fighting their way through waves of Sanctum forces.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}The unlikely duo's progress is halted by an impassable gate, which finally opens as if in response to Lightning's whispered words of apology.{Text NewLine}{Text 112}Did her plea reach the mind of the fal'Cie? Or was another being responsible for opening the portal?{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Sazh follows the ex-soldier into the Vestige, bemused by the lack of explanation, but driven on nonetheless by a purpose he has yet to reveal.";
"0032║$atar_exp_120p0" = "Military 'weapons' stalk the halls of the Vestige... Though the PSICOM recon team that uncovered the lowerworld being two days previous is still trapped inside, Lightning and Sazh know that the real threat is not a part of the Sanctum army, but the Pulse fal'Cie and its servant l'Cie.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Pulse l'Cie are former humans who have become agents of destruction. Those residents living near the Vestige face being Purged simply because of their proximity to the fal'Cie and the possibility that its power has bound them into servitude.";
"0033║$atar_exp_120p1" = "With tales of l'Cie haunting his thoughts, Hope hears Snow's voice calling in the distance.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Although he plans to confront Snow over his mother's death, the reality of the situation becomes too much for Hope to bear. He cannot go through with it. Not yet.";
"0034║$atar_exp_130p0" = "Pulse l'Cie are cursed beings who wield supernatural power and whose very existence incites panic and destruction.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Hope explodes into a rage upon hearing that Snow plans to rescue Serah, now a l'Cie herself. Even if she is Snow's fianc{Var85 200}e, nothing good can come of helping a sworn enemy of Cocoon. The situation only serves to magnify Hope's hatred of the man he holds responsible for his mother's death.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Shaking with fury, he is unable to form the words he so desperately wants to say.{Text NewLine}{Text 112}Oblivious to Hope's anger and worried for their safety, Snow decides to bring Hope and Vanille along on his mission.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Meanwhile, Sazh explains the cruel fate of a person cursed as a l'Cie. L'Cie are bound in eternal service to a fal'Cie, and failure to carry out a Focus results in transformation into a mindless abomination{Var85 87}a Cie'th.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}A person shackled by the l'Cie curse is beyond salvation.{Text NewLine}{Text 112}As Sazh comes to this grim conclusion, Lightning angrily compares him to those who insisted on the Purge. She knows full well the doom that awaits a l'Cie, and will do anything in her power to save her sister from that fate.";
"0035║$atar_exp_130p1" = "";
"0036║$atar_exp_140p0" = "A legend on Cocoon states that if l'Cie complete the Focus given by a fal'Cie, they turn into crystal and gain eternal life.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}And just as the legend describes, Serah, Lightning's younger sister and fianc{Var85 200}e to Snow, glows with an incredible light and turns into crystal. But has she truly gained eternal life? And what Focus has she completed?{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}This timeless crystal sleep seems nothing more than another form of death to Lightning, and she turns her feelings of grief and anger upon Snow.";
"0037║$atar_exp_140p1" = "Snow, however, refuses to give up hope of a future where Serah will return to him.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Just then, the Sanctum army begins its assault on the Vestige. Though it may mean sharing the Vestige's imminent destruction, the group heads ever deeper into the complex.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Snow seeks to persuade the fal'Cie to release his fianc{Var85 200}e, while Lightning and Sazh have other plans in mind...";
"0038║$atar_exp_145p0" = "Snow pleads with the Pulse fal'Cie. He offers himself in Serah's place if it will release her from her fate.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}The fal'Cie remains silent.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Seeing Snow's desperate pleas go unanswered, Lightning and Sazh draw weapons on the lowerworld being. Even if the fal'Cie will soon be destroyed along with the entire Vestige, they have reasons to defeat it with their own hands.{Text NewLine}{Text 112}They work together to bring down the fal'Cie, and the Vestige now plummets towards the lake below. A final wave of power explodes from the dying fal'Cie, transforming the water and surrounding area into solid crystal.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Lightning and the others do not witness this breathtaking event{Var85 87}upon defeating the fal'Cie, they are drawn through a rift into a dimension where an immense, otherworldly presence awaits.{Text NewLine}{Text 112}Onto their bodies, it sears cursed brands; onto their minds, the vision of a beast destroying Cocoon. Swept along by unimaginable energies, the helpless companions are swallowed in a lightless void.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}As Snow drifts in the darkness, one memory fights to the surface of his consciousness...";
"0039║$atar_exp_145p1" = "";
"0040║$atar_exp_150p0" = "Lightning feels nothing but anger towards the Pulse fal'Cie. It had taken Serah and cursed her with a l'Cie's doomed existence. It is the underlying reason for the Purge. And it is an enemy to be cut down if she is to fulfill Serah's final request: to save Cocoon.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Lightning's aggression provokes the fal'Cie into action, and it attacks her. Sazh draws his guns with grim resolve, and Snow joins the battle without hesitation.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}As they deal the killing blow to the master of the Vestige, a flash of light rends the air.";
"0041║$atar_exp_150p1" = "They are pulled into a swirling void of chaos, where they are bound by an ominous and inexorable entity. Branded with arcane markings, the companions are then assaulted with the vision of a terrible beast tearing Cocoon apart. Soon after, the Vestige finally succumbs to the combined attacks of the Sanctum forces.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}In the midst of the chaos, a memory surfaces from the depths of Snow's fading awareness: a marriage proposal made to his beloved Serah under a night sky lit with the colors of exploding fireworks. Can his wish for a happy future ever be granted now?";
"0042║$atar_exp_160p0" = "After being caught in the destruction of the Vestige, the group awakens directly under the Hanging Edge on the expanse of a solidified Lake Bresha. An aftereffect of the energies released by the dying fal'Cie, the waters of the lake are now frozen in crystal splendor.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Despite having survived a fall from an incredible height, the companions are unable to appreciate their luck as each one of them now bears a brand of alien design. The mark seared on their bodies signifies their servitude to a fal'Cie and the 'gift' of magical power.";
"0043║$atar_exp_160p1" = "It is the brand of a cursed l'Cie. Worse, they must now complete their assigned Focus if they are to avoid becoming monstrous Cie'th, though none can say for sure what their mission actually entails. Their only clue is the vision they all witnessed of the great beast laying waste to Cocoon.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Ragnarok.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Though all signs point to a bleak and tragic destiny, Snow alone remains optimistic. Convinced that his Focus is to grant Serah's wish and save Cocoon, he sets off full of confidence.";
"0044║$atar_exp_170p0" = "Now that they are Pulse l'Cie, Lightning and the others try to figure out what their Focus could be. The only thing they know for certain is that the rampaging beast Ragnarok is somehow involved.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Snow is convinced that their Focus is to protect their world by defeating the beast. But one fact contradicts his belief: Pulse l'Cie are the hated enemies of Cocoon. A Pulse fal'Cie would never assign such a task to its servants.";
"0045║$atar_exp_170p1" = "Lightning is infuriated by Snow's refusal to accept this logic. As she sees it, the fal'Cie not only made them into l'Cie, it also took her sister from her. The former soldier could never bring herself to meekly follow the orders of such a being, and Snow's apparent surrender to its will, however misinterpreted, is more than she can stand.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}As they trade heated words, Sanctum soldiers surround their location. Arguments will have to wait{Var85 87}for now, they must concentrate on surviving.";
"0046║$atar_exp_180p0" = "Is she dead, or merely sleeping?{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Serah, now a silent statue, is trapped in a crystal embrace. Lightning doesn't wish to leave her behind, but reluctantly says her farewells. The army is on their trail. If they stop to dig Serah free, their pursuers will certainly catch them.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}However, Snow is not ready to say good-bye. He elects to stay behind, protect Serah, and somehow fulfill her wish to save Cocoon.";
"0047║$atar_exp_180p1" = "Knowing they cannot change his mind, Lightning and the others continue on their way. Hope drags himself away from Snow for what might be the final time{Var85 87}and the chance to say what he is burning to say is lost.";
"0048║$atar_exp_190p0" = "Lightning and the others leave Snow behind with the crystallized Serah. As they continue their flight across the glassy expanse of Lake Bresha, the four companions spy a large contingent of Sanctum soldiers.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}In order to hunt down and exterminate the Purge fugitives, the government is mobilizing an inordinate number of troops. The excessive reaction is further proof of Cocoon's fear and hatred of Pulse. Even those who have barely come into contact with lowerworld elements cannot be permitted to exist.{Text NewLine}{Text 112}This all-consuming fear of some imagined corruption is the origin of the Purge. The entire population of a town was subjected to the Purge simply for living {Italic}near{Italic} the uncovered Pulse fal'Cie.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}It was Cocoon's citizens, in their terror, who allowed such an extreme policy to become a reality{Var85 87}the government simply acted in response to the will of the people. And Eden, the fal'Cie who guides the Sanctum, gave its tacit consent through silence.{Text NewLine}{Text 112}Now, after untold bloodshed, a military net is closing in around the fleeing l'Cie, driven by the clamoring of a panicked and angry populace.";
"0049║$atar_exp_190p1" = "";
"0050║$atar_exp_195p0" = "Lightning and the others are now cursed l'Cie. If they don't complete the Focus given to them by the fal'Cie, they are destined to become mindless Cie'th.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}But how can they complete a Focus that they don't understand?{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Their shared vision of the great beast Ragnarok laying waste to their world is their only clue. That, and the fact that Pulse l'Cie are held to be the mortal enemies of Cocoon...{Text NewLine}{Text 112}Could their Focus really be to orchestrate the destruction of their own home?{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Snow doesn't think so.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}He believes their task is to fulfill Serah's parting wish by keeping Cocoon safe. After all, wasn't she a l'Cie, just like them? His shaky logic only serves to infuriate Lightning, who holds him responsible for her sister's fate. Their confrontation is cut short by the arrival of their Sanctum pursuers.{Text NewLine}{Text 112}Having made their escape, Lightning and the others pass through the ruins of a city damaged several centuries ago in the war with Pulse.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Amidst the rubble, they happen upon an airship which they board in the hope of finally shaking the relentless army.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Snow, meanwhile, remains behind with the crystallized Serah...";
"0051║$atar_exp_195p1" = "";
"0052║$atar_exp_200p0" = "There is no doubt in Snow's mind.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}They may be Pulse l'Cie, but there is no way they can be enemies of Cocoon. Serah's last words before she turned to crystal are proof enough for him that their Focus is to defeat Ragnarok and protect their world.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Snow stays behind to defend his trapped fianc{Var85 200}e after Lightning and the others decide to continue onward.{Text NewLine}{Text 112}Brought to his knees by wave after wave of PSICOM soldiers during a protracted battle, the desperate young man is suddenly overcome by a strange phenomenon.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}The Twin Sisters of Shiva, Stiria and Nix, appear before him in a blinding flash of light. They easily dispatch the remaining troops, and then turn on Snow.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}He manages to defeat the icy Eidolons, but is soon captured by an unfamiliar Sanctum unit.{Text NewLine}{Text 112}A striking woman accompanies the soldiers{Var85 87}a woman with a l'Cie brand.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Meanwhile, try as they might, Lightning's group cannot shake their determined pursuers. Crippled by enemy fire, their airship plummets towards the ground...";
"0053║$atar_exp_200p1" = "";
"0054║$atar_exp_210p0" = "Their airship damaged during the escape from the army, the l'Cie are forced to make a crash landing in the Vile Peaks.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Accustomed to the rigors of conflict, Lightning immediately sets off to outdistance any pursuit, trailed by Hope.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Exhausted and on the brink of despair, Sazh cannot bring himself to follow. He knows the army will never stop chasing them. And even if they do somehow evade capture, they face transformation into Cie'th. How can they complete a Focus they don't understand?{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Despite the futility of the situation, Sazh cannot leave Vanille to fend for herself, and he forces his reluctant legs to carry him onward.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Far ahead of the others, Lightning recalls a conversation with her old superior, Lieutenant Amodar, in which he had warned her not to get involved with anything connected to the lowerworld. She, of course, subsequently chose not to heed his warning, and after confronting the Pulse fal'Cie found herself branded a l'Cie.{Text NewLine}{Text 112}Now, anger smolders within her. Anger at her transformation into a l'Cie, anger at being forced to flee like a fugitive, and anger at herself for allowing it all to happen.";
"0055║$atar_exp_210p1" = "";
"0056║$atar_exp_220p0" = "The Sanctum announces that the Pulse fal'Cie and any civilians who may have come into contact with its influence are to be deported to the world below.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Knowing that Serah is being held by the offending creature, Lightning reasons that the only way to reach her sister before they are exiled is to board the train and be Purged herself. After coming to this conclusion, she acts without hesitation. She knows the risks, but there are some things you just have to do...";
"0057║$atar_exp_220p1" = "As Hope listens to Lightning's tale, he begins to realize how different they are. He knows he doesn't have the strength to charge into certain danger, even if he has no other choice. Unable to keep up with the battle-hardened soldier, Hope falls into despair.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Meanwhile, Sazh and Vanille fight their way along a different route. Like Lightning, Sazh had joined the Purge voluntarily, but now he simply acts as fear and despair prompt him, his former resolve seemingly forgotten.";
"0058║$atar_exp_230p0" = "As a resident of Palumpolum, Hope should never have been a candidate for the Purge. The radical government policy only concerns the inhabitants of the town of Bodhum.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Unfortunately for Hope and his mother, the Sanctum announces the Purge on the day they are visiting the coastal community{Var85 87}and the Sanctum soldiers rounding up the deportees make no distinction between locals and visitors.";
"0059║$atar_exp_230p1" = "Later, at the Hanging Edge, Hope's mother is killed in the violence which erupts when the true nature of the Purge is revealed.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}This indirectly leads to Hope's encounter with the Pulse fal'Cie, and transformation into a cursed l'Cie.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Now, he rails against his cruel fate. He curses the government that started the Purge, the fal'Cie who made him a l'Cie, the army that hunts him like a criminal...{Text NewLine}{Text 112}But most of all, he chokes on the hatred he feels for Snow{Var85 87}the man responsible for dragging his mother into the battle that claimed her life.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Sazh wants to help Hope return home to his father. The boy shows little enthusiasm for a family reunion, but Sazh is insistent.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}He knows how it feels to be a dad.";
"0060║$atar_exp_240p0" = "The War of Transgression{Var85 87}the conflict between Pulse and Cocoon.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}A towering wreck is all that remains of a lowerworld airship shot down during the battle that took place centuries before...{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}At that time, forces from Pulse attempted to invade Cocoon only to be repelled by the efforts of the Sanctum fal'Cie{Var85 87}though not before the invaders had rent a great wound in the floating world's shell.";
"0061║$atar_exp_240p1" = "Though Sanctum fal'Cie subsequently repaired the damage using debris from the surface of their routed enemies' planet, the psychological wounds inflicted by the conflict are evident even now in the Cocoon citizen's unreasoning fear of all things Pulse.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}And reminders of the lowerworld threat still remain. Mechanical terrors brought in with the debris replace their rusting parts and wander the area, while government troops struggle to contain them.{Text NewLine}{Text 112}The Pulse fal'Cie buried in Bodhum may have arrived in the same fashion, sleeping away the years until its eventual discovery.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}With lowerworld terrors lurking in every shadow, Sazh creeps forward, doing his best to shield Vanille and Hope...";
"0062║$atar_exp_250p0" = "Lightning says little of her feelings, but Sazh senses her frustration. Despite braving the dangers of the Purge and the Vestige in an effort to save her sister, Lightning was helpless to prevent Serah's transformation into crystal. Now she is forced to flee as a fugitive{Var85 87}a Pulse l'Cie and hated enemy of Cocoon.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}And then there is their Focus. If they don't complete the task they have yet to figure out, they face transformation into mindless Cie'th. Should they fulfill their Focus, eternal crystal slumber is the only reward.";
"0063║$atar_exp_250p1" = "And should they stop too long to ponder their fate, they risk capture and execution at the hands of the relentless Sanctum army.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}All roads seem to lead to despair{Var85 87}something Sazh understands only too well. The question is: will Lightning help them find a way out of their hopeless situation?{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Unbeknownst to Sazh, the answer has already begun to form in her mind...";
"0064║$atar_exp_260p0" = "Lightning makes a decision.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}The Pulse fal'Cie transformed her and Serah into l'Cie. The Sanctum fal'Cie, Eden, directs the army hunting her down.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Pulse or Sanctum, 'fal'Cie' means one thing to Lightning: an enemy responsible for ruining their lives. A clear-cut enemy is something she can deal with. Having a target is something she can understand.";
"0065║$atar_exp_260p1" = "The former soldier means to infiltrate the Sanctum capital, and take out the fal'Cie Eden.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}She knows her plan is reckless. It could be disastrous for Cocoon, and flies in the face of Serah's last wish. It could even end in battle against Snow, who will do anything to save Cocoon. But it is the only path that will satisfy her rage.{Text NewLine}{Text 112}Sazh and Vanille oppose her idea, but Hope embraces the opportunity. This is his chance to grow stronger and finally confront Snow.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Lightning is done running away.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Now she runs forward, her mind set on toppling the Sanctum. But even Lightning cannot foresee how this journey will end...";
"0066║$atar_exp_270p0" = "Hope makes a choice to fight alongside Lightning, but quickly finds himself exhausted by the pace.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Lightning grows ever more agitated. Their enemy is the Sanctum army. She cannot afford to look after the straggling Hope while she faces such a dangerous foe. Losing all patience, Lightning curses his weakness and tries to leave him behind.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}In that moment, her l'Cie brand burns with radiant pain.";
"0067║$atar_exp_270p1" = "As if to strike down obstacles in Lightning's path, the Eidolon Odin appears and attacks the bewildered Hope.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Lightning moves without thinking. She blocks the deadly blade aimed at the boy she meant to abandon moments before.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Lightning defeats Odin, and brings the entity under her command. Why did the Eidolon appear in the first place?{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}There is no answer to her question, but one thing is certain: she no longer wishes to leave Hope to survive on his own.";
"0068║$atar_exp_280p0" = "Sazh and Vanille decide against joining Lightning in her vendetta against the Sanctum, though doing so leaves them without a road to follow. It seems all they can do is keep running. And then there is Hope to worry about. But he'll surely grow tired of the fighting and make his way home{Var85 87}won't he?{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Sazh also harbors another fear: with the entirety of Cocoon in an uproar over the recent Pulse activity, any incident involving l'Cie could spark a full-scale panic. After all, not even Sazh can shake his dread of the lowerworld.";
"0069║$atar_exp_280p1" = "If Cocoon is to know peace, he argues, l'Cie like them all need to die.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Even as the words pass his lips, he immediately regrets giving voice to such sentiments, suddenly aware of his companion's feelings on the matter. But Vanille just smiles bravely, and urges Sazh to keep on moving.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}They have to stay ahead of the army if they want to survive.";
"0070║$atar_exp_290p0" = "As Lightning and the others make their way through the Vile Peaks, Snow is escorted aboard the airship {Italic}Lindblum{Italic} after his capture at Lake Bresha.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}His captors are members of the Wide-area Response Brigade, otherwise known as the 'Cavalry.' The Cavalry is not directly involved with the Purge or the tracking down of l'Cie.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Nevertheless, their commander, Brigadier General Raines, calmly explains the reasons behind the Sanctum and PSICOM operations, and their plans to hold a public execution.";
"0071║$atar_exp_290p1" = "If the l'Cie are killed in plain sight of the populace, he asserts, the panic threatening the stability of their society will be defused. Are Raines and the Cavalry also tools of the Sanctum?{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}And who is the woman who works with them? Isn't she a Pulse l'Cie and enemy of Cocoon?{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Full of questions and unsure of his captors' motives, Snow recalls another time when he felt this powerless{Var85 87}a time when one cold fact robbed him of the strength to stand.{Text NewLine}{Text 112}It was the moment he learned that his beloved Serah was a Pulse l'Cie.";
"0072║$atar_exp_300p0" = "If l'Cie were machines, they would seek to complete any Focus without question. But l'Cie are human. And no human willingly desires the slavery imposed by a fal'Cie.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Sazh and Vanille support each other in their desperate flight. What is their Focus? They are scared to even contemplate the answer to that question.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Snow, by contrast, chooses to pursue his objective without hesitation, not because he wants to obey the fal'Cie, but because it is Serah's wish.";
"0073║$atar_exp_300p1" = "He believes without the slightest shred of doubt that his Focus is to protect Cocoon.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Lightning and Hope, meanwhile, choose to fight. They turn their anger against an unjust fate and a world hostile to their very existence.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}On their way to Eden at the very heart of Cocoon, Lightning and Hope prepare to enter a military-controlled zone...";
"0074║$atar_exp_310p0" = "Rejecting the fate chosen for her by the fal'Cie and set on exacting revenge on her cold-blooded government, Lightning enters the Gapra Whitewood along with Hope.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}It seems they've managed to lose their PSICOM trackers, but the Whitewood is a Sanctum military zone, and their chances of encountering hostile units are high. Yet what choice do they have? It's the only road that leads to the Sanctum capital.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Lightning now intends to fight on Hope's behalf after Odin's appearance forces her to rethink her decision to leave the boy behind.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}But she isn't the only one to have had a change of heart.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Having relied on Lightning for protection from the beginning, Hope resolves not to flinch from danger, choosing instead to put himself squarely in the line of fire.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Sensing the shift in his attitude, Lightning entrusts the lead to her young companion.";
"0075║$atar_exp_310p1" = "";
"0076║$atar_exp_320p0" = "Taking the lead of his own free will, Hope precedes Lightning into the depths of the Gapra Whitewood.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}He needs to be stronger.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Hope joins Lightning in her fight against the Sanctum because he thinks the experience of battle will toughen him up.{Text NewLine}{Text 112}He cannot show fear. He cannot show weakness.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}If he does, he's afraid Lightning will decide to go on without him again. So, even if it is a lie, he puts on a brave face, and pushes his terror aside.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Seeing that he is struggling to control his fear, Lightning gives Hope a knife in an attempt to boost his confidence.";
"0077║$atar_exp_330p0" = "A Woodlands Observation Battalion patrol passes by. Strangely enough, the soldiers don't appear to be looking for intruders.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}From her own experience as a soldier, Lightning realizes why: these troops still don't know about the l'Cie fugitives.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}PSICOM, wishing to cover their failure to exterminate them in the Vile Peaks, is suppressing information. As an elite unit under the direct command of the Sanctum, PSICOM has its reputation to consider.";
"0078║$atar_exp_330p1" = "That pride has left a hole in the security net for Lightning and Hope to sneak through.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}It seems their journey through the Gapra Whitewood will be easier than expected. After all the ill fortune that has befallen them so far, they're certainly due some luck...";
"0079║$atar_exp_340p0" = "Thanks to PSICOM's reluctance to share intelligence, the security level of the Gapra Whitewood is comparatively low.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Now that they have a little space to breathe, Lightning and Hope ponder the fates of their fellow l'Cie. Sazh and Vanille must still be on the run. And who knows how Snow must be faring?{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Out of the blue, Hope asks Lightning why Snow's gang calls itself NORA.";
"0080║$atar_exp_340p1" = "Though puzzled by his sudden interest, Lightning supplies him with the answer: it's an acronym that stands for 'No Obligations, Rules, or Authority.' They wish to live without restrictions, she explains, though some might argue that what they {Italic}really{Italic} wish to live without is responsibility.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Hope's face darkens at this explanation. Spurred by his agitation, he hurries onwards through the waiting gate. Where's an enemy when you need one? He needs an outlet for the anger that suddenly threatens to consume him.";
"0081║$atar_exp_350p0" = "Lightning learns the reason for Hope's animosity towards Snow: his mother's death during the chaos of the Purge. Believing the responsibility to lie with the NORA leader, the grief-stricken boy has been feeding his rage ever since. Hope's motivation for joining Lightning in her vendetta is to experience battle and grow strong enough to challenge Snow.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}The blade in Hope's hand shines brightly. Will the gift Lightning gave him to boost his confidence become the instrument of his revenge?";
"0082║$atar_exp_350p1" = "The weapon Hope stares at so intently awakens memories in his companion.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}On Lightning's birthday, Serah confessed to her sister that she had become a Pulse l'Cie. Not willing to believe the story, Lightning pushed Serah away with disdainful words. By the time she discovered that Serah had been telling the truth, it was too late...{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Now the knife is all she has left of her sister{Var85 87}a birthday gift, and symbol of unbearable regret.";
"0083║$atar_exp_360p0" = "As Hope reaches out a hand to a fallen soldier, Lightning stops him with a harsh reminder: they have chosen the path of war. They will face many soldiers on the way, and it's kill or be killed. If you allow yourself to be controlled by compassion, if you allow yourself to falter, then you are lost. Lightning teaches Hope a strategy for removing hesitation: decide upon a goal, and shut out everything else.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Hope takes these words to heart, and comes up with Operation Nora. Named after his dead mother, it is the means by which he will exact vengeance upon Snow.";
"0084║$atar_exp_360p1" = "Though he knows it won't bring his mother back, it's nevertheless something he needs to do.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Lightning soon realizes her mistake. Her lecture to abandon compassion was intended as a warning against the hesitation she fears will be his undoing, but he has clearly interpreted it as a cue to hurl himself headlong into harm's way.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Regretting her words, Lightning continues on through the Whitewood.";
"0085║$atar_exp_370p0" = "Hope now concentrates all his efforts on Operation Nora{Var85 87}his plan for taking revenge against Snow.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Though she feels responsible for his newly acquired recklessness in battle, Lightning finds herself unable to say anything. She is afraid that if she prevents Hope from fighting, he will lose the drive he needs to keep going, and succumb to despair.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Not knowing how to reach Hope, Lightning rescinds her earlier decision and suggests they visit the boy's father in Palumpolum.";
"0086║$atar_exp_370p1" = "Meanwhile, Snow struggles with his conscience as he prepares to help the Cavalry track down the other Pulse l'Cie. Snow swore to do whatever it takes to save Cocoon. What has happened to make him act against that promise?{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Now clear of the Vile Peaks, Sazh and Vanille approach a stretch of beautiful countryside that promises an easier road to travel.";
"0087║$atar_exp_380p0" = "As they flee with no particular destination in mind, Sazh and Vanille spot warships passing overhead. The military craft appear to be flying in the direction of Palumpolum. Lightning and Hope were heading towards that city...{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Could the army have found them?{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Though Sazh is worried for his former companions' safety, he knows that any attempt to rescue them from Sanctum troops would be suicide. Still, they can't just walk away{Var85 87}can they?{Text NewLine}{Text 112}Sensing Sazh's uncertainty, Vanille swiftly agrees that there isn't much they can do, and suggests they run. Reasoning that it would be best to put as much distance between themselves and the army as possible, she suggests heading in the opposite direction{Var85 87}towards the city of Nautilus.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}And so Vanille skips off through the dappled shade of the Sunleth Waterscape, only too eager to put danger behind them once more.";
"0088║$atar_exp_390p0" = "Sazh and Vanille make their way through the Sunleth Waterscape, trying to distance themselves from the Sanctum forces assembling in the city of Palumpolum.{Text NewLine}Vanille's offhand question about family fills Sazh's head with memories of his son, Dajh...{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}As fireworks illuminated the night sky with brilliant color, Dajh had made a wish out of concern for his dad. Touched by the insight of his little boy, Sazh smiled, pretending to be cheerful{Var85 87}but all the while an unbearable pain gnawed at his soul.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}This pain plagues him even now. But what is the reason for Sazh's misery? And who is the enigmatic woman with a more than passing interest in the boy and his father?";
"0089║$atar_exp_400p0" = "With a heavy heart, Sazh reveals the fate that has befallen his son, Dajh.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}When Pulse l'Cie invaders attacked the fal'Cie powering the Euride Gorge energy plant, it chose the closest human to become its servant and defender: a small boy who had wandered into the facility. Now a Sanctum l'Cie with the ability to sense the presence of Pulsian energies, Dajh has been held in custody and monitored by government officials ever since.";
"0090║$atar_exp_400p1" = "It is thanks to Dajh's unique ability that PSICOM was able to discover the Pulse fal'Cie in Bodhum. However, with his exact Focus yet to be determined, the boy is doomed to become a Cie'th.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}This is what prompted Sazh to board the Purge train. Guessing that Dajh's Focus might be to destroy the Pulse fal'Cie, Sazh seized the only means available to him to reach the accursed creature before it could be carried to the world below. If he could slay it somehow, he reasoned, he might just be able to save his son.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}So, now that the Pulse fal'Cie is no more, has Dajh gone through the same crystal transformation as Serah? Or was his Focus not to rid the world of the fal'Cie, but of the l'Cie servants it created?{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}If that is the case, then Sazh and his companions must die to spare Dajh a fate worse than death.";
"0091║$atar_exp_410p0" = "Sazh's son, Dajh, was branded a Sanctum l'Cie when he stumbled into the midst of a Pulse attack on the Euride Gorge energy plant.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}With the help of the l'Cie powers Dajh gained during the incident, the military discovered the Pulse fal'Cie in Bodhum, instigating the Purge. In the ensuing violence, Hope lost his mother, and Lightning and Snow witnessed Serah's transformation into crystal.";
"0092║$atar_exp_410p1" = "The whole series of events that has thrown their lives into chaos and threatens even now to shatter Cocoon's peaceful society can be traced back to Euride.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Had that incident never occurred, could these tragedies have been avoided? Who can say? There is little point lamenting that which cannot be changed.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Yet though the past cannot be changed, it {Italic}can{Italic} be forgotten{Var85 87}for a while, at least{Var85 87}and so Sazh and Vanille make their way to Nautilus, 'City of Dreams,' as storm clouds gather overhead.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Meanwhile, Lightning and Hope enter one of the largest cities on Cocoon{Var85 87}as quite another kind of storm approaches...";
"0093║$atar_exp_420p0" = "With events spiraling out of control, the Sanctum army mobilizes all the forces under its command in an attempt to apprehend the Pulse l'Cie and thereby prevent Cocoon from descending into chaos. Prioritizing its mission over its reputation, PSICOM accordingly enlists the aid of the local Guardian Corps soldiers.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Under the general command of Colonel Rosch, units of troops occupy positions across Palumpolum in anticipation of a l'Cie attack.";
"0094║$atar_exp_420p1" = "Originally planning to take the Eden-bound train from inside the city, Lightning is now having second thoughts. She can't help but feel concern when she sees the rage-fueled Hope throwing himself into battle. It doesn't help that it was Lightning herself who inadvertently encouraged him to concentrate on his goal of revenge in the first place.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}And that goal is what drives him now. He must complete Operation Nora, and make Snow and the Sanctum pay for the death of his mother. But who can say how much time remains for a l'Cie who ignores his Focus?{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Ignorant of her worries, Hope leads Lightning to an underground complex that will allow them to sneak past the Guardian Corps troops and into the city.";
"0095║$atar_exp_430p0" = "Under the command of Colonel Rosch, PSICOM and the Guardian Corps occupy positions across Palumpolum in anticipation of a l'Cie attack.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}In order to avoid the increased security, Lightning and Hope travel through an underground complex that reaches far beneath the city. If they can enter the town undetected, they should be able to find a way to reach Eden{Var85 87}the capital that lies at the heart of Cocoon.";
"0096║$atar_exp_430p1" = "Hope hurries onwards, eager to continue Operation Nora, and exact revenge on Snow and the Sanctum.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Yet l'Cie who fail to complete their Focus become Cie'th. It's uncertain when the exact moment of transformation will come, but time is not on their side. Even though there may be no light at the end of the tunnel, they have no choice but to keep trudging along in the dark.{Text NewLine}{Text 112}Hope's grim determination is a source of pain for Lightning. Her attempt at giving him a reason to survive has backfired, fanning the flames of his hatred and setting him on the path to a deadly confrontation.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}He is her responsibility. She has to protect him.";
"0097║$atar_exp_440p0" = "The Sanctum fal'Cie treat the people of Cocoon like pets. Upon realizing this fact, Lightning comes to understand herself. Since the moment she was born, she was raised under fal'Cie care. Sheltered and protected, she never realized how much she depended on them. But after becoming a Pulse l'Cie, she is removed from that protection.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}And like a child separated from her mother, she wanders in confusion and doubt. Added to the anxiety of being a fugitive, the grief of losing Serah, and her rage at an unjust fate, Lightning finds herself on the brink of blackest despair.";
"0098║$atar_exp_440p1" = "It is all so clear now. Thinking of a future without hope would be too much to bear, so she made the Sanctum her enemy and sought to lose herself in mindless combat. But it was all just a way to avoid facing reality.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}And now she's got Hope doing the same.{Text NewLine}If he loses himself in revenge, he may gain temporary respite from the horror of his predicament{Var85 87}but it will solve nothing.{Text NewLine}{Text 112}Overcome by guilt, Lightning tells Hope to abandon Operation Nora, much to the boy's disbelief. If he gives up on revenge, what else is there to live for?{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}The two l'Cie have much to think about...";
"0099║$atar_exp_450p0" = "Lightning knows that Snow is not Hope's favorite person. But the only way to ensure the boy's escape from the swarm of Sanctum troops is to leave him with the man he despises.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Her mind made up, Lightning shoves Hope at Snow, then charges the enemy soldiers, intending to cut a path through which they can escape. She may have failed to give him hope, but the least she can do is keep him alive{Var85 87}even if that means sacrificing herself.";
"0100║$atar_exp_450p1" = "After appearing out of nowhere with an Eidolon and felling soldiers left and right, Snow explains how the Cavalry picked him up. The rebel brigade is part of the Sanctum army, but it seems they have plans to topple the government with the help of the l'Cie.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Hope, of course, couldn't care less. The man responsible for his mother's death stands right in front of him. Operation Nora might be over, but his rage will not be satisfied by mere words.{Text NewLine}{Text 112}As Hope runs through streets sheathed in Shiva's ice, he can feel the shape of the knife Lightning left in his care nestled against his side...";
"0101║$atar_exp_460p0" = "Colonel Rosch, PSICOM Director in command of l'Cie operations, decides to escalate the military presence in Palumpolum. Authorizing open warfare in the streets while civilians are still being evacuated is inviting disaster, but he is willing to make that sacrifice.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}If the l'Cie are not put down here and now, the Pulse-phobic populace will reach boiling point: Cocoon's towns will erupt in riots, and the loss of life will be staggering.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Meanwhile, the l'Cie{Var85 87}who are currently split into two groups{Var85 87}choose Hope's house as a rendezvous point. But will they all make it?";
"0102║$atar_exp_460p1" = "Every word that the oblivious Snow says feeds the flames of Hope's anger. Has Snow forgotten what he's done? Has he {Italic}forgotten{Italic} how he got Hope's mother killed? Hope's patience has finally run out.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}During a radio conversation with Lightning, he states his intention to carry out Operation Nora...and take his revenge. With that, the line goes dead.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Lightning tries to reason with Hope, but her desperate plea never reaches him.";
"0103║$atar_exp_470p0" = "The hellish lowerworld feared by every citizen of Cocoon is known to Fang as Gran Pulse. On the way to Hope's home, she begins relating her past in response to Lightning's probing.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Fang reveals that she is a l'Cie from Gran Pulse{Var85 87}the world below the floating shell of Cocoon. After completing a Focus, she had turned to crystal.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}When she awoke, Fang found herself very far from home in the nest of her enemies. And she was not alone{Var85 87}Vanille, a fellow Gran Pulse l'Cie, was with her.";
"0104║$atar_exp_470p1" = "Meanwhile, in another part of the city, Snow and Hope spy a group of Palumpolum civilians being herded by Sanctum troops. The government means to Purge them too...{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Thinking to rescue the people from that fate, Snow leaps into action, ever the cheerful hero{Var85 87}but this serves only to further agitate Hope.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}What does a l'Cie with no hope for the future have to smile about? Shaking his head in disgust, Hope awaits an opportunity to take his revenge.";
"0105║$atar_exp_480p0" = "Snow has seen the merciless nature of the Sanctum army. {Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}The military's goal is not the protection of civilians{Var85 87}it is the extermination of l'Cie. As long as the Pulse servants are killed, the number of innocent deaths is inconsequential.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Snow threatens the citizens, hoping to make them run as far away as possible, and thus protect them from ending their days as 'collateral damage.'";
"0106║$atar_exp_480p1" = "But his good intentions are misunderstood.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}An angry mob tracks down the two l'Cie, and advances on them with a mix of trepidation and determination. They believe they are doing the right thing{Var85 87}that they are standing up in defense of their homes.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}The scene reminds Hope just how much everyone on Cocoon hates l'Cie. Hates {Italic}him{Italic}. Coming face-to-face with this cruel reality, Hope falls ever deeper into despair. Even if he makes it back to his home in Felix Heights, there is no salvation waiting for him there.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}His mother, Nora, is no longer around to shield him from the dangers of the world.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Snow saw to that.";
"0107║$atar_exp_490p0" = "Hope finally unleashes the anger he has been feeding for so long. Channeling his hate into deadly power, he blasts Snow with fiery magic. But just as he prepares to deal the killing blow, he is hurled from the roof of the building they are standing on by a nearby explosion.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Snow doesn't hesitate for a second. He hasn't forgotten the dying wish of a mother who fell during the violence of the Purge. Catching the boy he now knows is her son, Snow shields Hope with his own body as they crash to the ground below.";
"0108║$atar_exp_490p1" = "Elsewhere, Lightning listens as Fang makes a confession...{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}When Fang and Vanille awoke from crystal stasis, they had no memory of their past. Thinking it might give them a hint about their Focus, they decided to attack the Sanctum fal'Cie in Euride Gorge.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Unfortunately, Fang left the scene none the wiser, and is still desperately trying to figure out their task in order to prevent Vanille from becoming a Cie'th{Var85 87}and to stop the creation of any more l'Cie.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}The Gran Pulse native then reveals that she believes Serah was chosen by the fal'Cie to carry out the Focus they no longer remember.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Lightning takes the news with mixed emotions. Fang deserves to pay for what happened to Serah. But at the same time, she gives Lightning hope{Var85 87}her sister may not be a crystal forever.";
"0109║$atar_exp_500p0" = "Just as the citizens of Lightning's world fear the lowerworld of Pulse, the people of 'Gran' Pulse{Var85 87}as Fang calls her home{Var85 87}fear the floating nest of vipers that is Cocoon.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}It would seem the two women are not so different. They each grew up in fear of another world, bear the mark of a Pulse l'Cie, have a Focus they don't understand, and live as fugitives from the Sanctum.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}But unlike Lightning, Fang has not given up hope. She still plans to track down Vanille, finish their Focus, and then get back to Gran Pulse.";
"0110║$atar_exp_500p1" = "Hearing this, Lightning laments the fact that she has no plan and no reason to keep fighting. Fang responds that she has all the reason anyone could need: to stay alive until Serah wakes up from her crystal sleep.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}As Lightning comes around to this idea, there is an explosion in the distance. Could Snow and Hope be in trouble? Trading worried glances, the two l'Cie race off in the direction of the fighting.";
"0111║$atar_exp_510p0" = "Hope regains consciousness to find himself being carried on Snow's broad back.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}The self-styled 'hero' staggers under the boy's weight as he forces his wounded body forward. Pausing to rest, he talks about the anguish and guilt he hides behind a cheerful mask{Var85 87}before returning the knife to Hope's hand.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}The NORA leader is defenseless. With one thrust, Hope can finally claim vengeance for his mother's death. This is the moment the boy has fought for. His chance for revenge.{Text NewLine}But Hope hesitates and then the moment is gone.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Hope reveals that he always knew killing Snow wouldn't bring his mother back, but that he had no choice but to cling to that goal. He didn't survive this long to see revenge{Var85 87}he saw revenge as a means to survive.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}It is his hatred of Snow that has sustained him through countless battles. In a strange way, the man who made a promise to his mother has been protecting him all along.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}When he is later reunited with Lightning, Hope tells her that Operation Nora is over, and gives her back the knife. He doesn't need it anymore.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Having avoided further military pursuit, the group finally arrives at the Estheim household, where Hope breaks the terrible news to his anxious father...";
"0112║$atar_exp_510p1" = "";
"0113║$atar_exp_520p0" = "The knife Serah gave her on her birthday has become a symbol of regret for Lightning.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Because she refused to believe her sister's story that day, Serah ended up a prisoner of the Pulse fal'Cie, and Lightning herself became a l'Cie when she later tried to save her. Since then, the former soldier has sought out battle to avoid dealing with the guilt she feels for turning her sister away.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Now, however, Lightning finally faces the truth of her emotions, and accepts responsibility for her part in what happened.";
"0114║$atar_exp_520p1" = "She meekly apologizes to the injured Snow{Var85 87}the man who always believed in Serah, and protected Hope from harm.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}The rifts between the l'Cie are healing, but the reality of their situation is still grim. When Snow talks about taking down the Sanctum, Hope's father, Bartholomew, points out the flaws in their plan.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}If the government is toppled by l'Cie, how will the people react? Will they not see their worst fears realized, take up arms, and hasten the very cataclysm they wish to avoid?{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}As the l'Cie ponder their strategy, PSICOM commandos burst into the house. Hope stands against the soldiers, while the wounded Snow takes care of his father.";
"0115║$atar_exp_530p0" = "Colonel Rosch, Director of PSICOM, explains the necessity of his actions to the l'Cie, declaring that the Sanctum's{Var85 87}and the fal'Cie's{Var85 87}decision to order the Purge was anything but arbitrary. Had they not initiated such measures, he contends, and ignored the cries of the people, Cocoon's panicked society would have torn itself apart.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}If Rosch speaks the truth, then the l'Cie's enemy is not the government, but millions of Cocoon civilians. Yet even if this is so, they must somehow find a way to survive.";
"0116║$atar_exp_530p1" = "Overcoming his desire for revenge, Hope sets out in search of a new goal. Somewhere beyond the maelstrom of hatred and the grasping will of the fal'Cie is the future they search for. Hope bids farewell to his father, and boards the Cavalry airship.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Elsewhere, Sazh and Vanille are still on the run. The two fugitives wander aimlessly, riding the currents of fate to the doorstep of the City of Dreams...";
"0117║$atar_exp_540p0" = "Nautilus, the City of Dreams{Var85 87}the biggest theme park on Cocoon{Var85 87}is crowded with tourists. If Sazh and Vanille can lose themselves in this crush of people, the army will never find them. Even so, Sazh finds it hard to feel relieved.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}His son, Dajh, has been made into a l'Cie after wandering into an incident at Euride Gorge. But unlike his father, he is now a servant of a Sanctum fal'Cie and an enemy of Pulse. As he is locked away under the watchful eye of PSICOM, Sazh has no way of knowing how his son is doing.";
"0118║$atar_exp_540p1" = "If Dajh's Focus was to destroy the Pulse fal'Cie in the Bodhum Vestige, then he should already have turned into crystal...{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}But what if his Focus was to kill the Pulse l'Cie? Sazh and his companions would have to die to save Dajh from becoming a Cie'th.{Text NewLine}And one other thing is gnawing at his mind:{Text NewLine}after telling Vanille about his son's situation, the ever-cheerful girl has completely lost her spark.";
"0119║$atar_exp_550p0" = "A newsflash is broadcast throughout Nautilus.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}During the scenes of combat shown from Palumpolum, Vanille catches a glimpse of Fang. Although it's the first she's seen of her friend since they were separated at Euride Gorge, Vanille finds it hard to give in to her joy. Not after what Sazh has said about his son.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Dajh is now a Sanctum l'Cie{Var85 87}a sworn enemy of his father. And she is directly responsible.";
"0120║$atar_exp_550p1" = "If Fang and Vanille hadn't attacked the fal'Cie at the energy plant, the creature would never have chosen the nearby Dajh as a l'Cie. The young woman is overwhelmed by guilt.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Ignorant of Vanille's involvement, Sazh attempts to cheer her up, but his misplaced kindness only makes her feel worse.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}The parade is about to begin. For now, she will lose herself in its dream, knowing that when it is over, the suffering she has been running from will finally catch up with her.";
"0121║$atar_exp_560p0" = "The Pompa Sancta parade is a spectacle of light and sound that commemorates the war between Cocoon and Pulse.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}An embodiment of evil, the Pulse l'Cie appears with plans for the total destruction of Cocoon. Hard-pressed by a Sanctum l'Cie, the lowerworld servant takes the form of an infernal beast{Var85 87}a shape meant to resemble the monstrous Ragnarok.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}The final battle ensues, and the Pulse l'Cie is defeated. It could almost be a foreshadowing of how events may truly unfold...";
"0122║$atar_exp_560p1" = "While other onlookers are transported by a dream of the past, Vanille is yanked into the present by a nightmarish vision of the future. The two l'Cie hurry away in the direction of Nautilus Park.";
"0123║$atar_exp_570p0" = "Tired of fleeing with no hope in sight, Sazh quietly says his good-byes to Vanille.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}He intends to give himself up to the army and beg PSICOM to let him talk to his son. Even if it ends in his execution, it will all be worth it if he can see Dajh one more time and tell him about his encounter with the Nautilus Park chocobos.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Not willing to let Sazh just give up and die, Vanille tries to talk him out of it. Revenge is her best bet.{Text NewLine}{Text 112}If she reveals the identity of the culprit behind the Euride Gorge incident that sealed the fate of both father and son, then maybe Sazh will have something to live for.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}The culprit, of course, is Vanille herself. But how to explain...? As the young woman searches for the right words, sniper bullets bite into the ground around them.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Sazh covers Vanille as they run for the exit.{Text NewLine}It's all fine if he gets captured by the army, but he has to help Vanille escape.";
"0124║$atar_exp_570p1" = "";
"0125║$atar_exp_580p0" = "Upon becoming a Sanctum l'Cie, Dajh gained the ability to sense the presence of Pulse beings. With the help of his powers, the fal'Cie that had slumbered for centuries in Bodhum was subsequently discovered on the night of the fireworks display.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Since that time, no one has been able to work out what Dajh's Focus actually is, but now it reveals itself in the cruelest manner possible. He uses his sensory ability to track down the fugitive Pulse l'Cie{Var85 87}and turns to crystal the instant he embraces his father. It seems the boy's task was to capture the servants of lowerworld fal'Cie.";
"0126║$atar_exp_580p1" = "As Sazh collapses in shock and despair, Colonel Nabaat, the PSICOM officer supervising Dajh, appears before him. With sadistic glee, his captor at last reveals the truth to the distraught Sazh: that one of the people responsible for his son becoming a l'Cie has been at his side all along. {Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Vanille flees and Sazh gives chase.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Colonel Nabaat does nothing to stop them. Just think of the data they could collect by watching l'Cie fight each other...";
"0127║$atar_exp_590p0" = "Sazh loses his will to go on.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}With his beloved son transformed into crystal, he has nothing left to live for. He curses Vanille for her part in the tragedy, but killing her won't bring Dajh back.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Sazh's brand suddenly glows with burning intensity, and the Eidolon Brynhildr appears before the despairing father. He doesn't even try to run. Maybe death is the easiest path.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}But then Vanille puts herself between them.{Text NewLine}Sazh may despise her for what she's done, but she can't let him die. Once the Eidolon is defeated, Sazh turns his gun on Vanille. Unable to shoot the young woman, he then turns the gun on himself...{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Soon after, Vanille becomes a prisoner of PSICOM. She faces transportation to Eden and public execution{Var85 87}the Sanctum's chosen doom for Pulse l'Cie.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Watching a news broadcast on board the {Italic}Lindblum{Italic}, the Cavalry's flagship, Lightning and the other l'Cie learn of the impending execution...";
"0128║$atar_exp_590p1" = "";
"0129║$atar_exp_600p0" = "{Text NewLine}The Sanctum plans to transport its l'Cie prisoners to Eden, then carry out their execution before a public audience.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Brigadier General Raines, the Cavalry commander, suggests that by showing the deaths of the Pulse 'monsters,' the Sanctum fal'Cie hope to quell rising panic and reaffirm their dominion over society.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Lightning and the others can't stand by and let their companions be sacrificed to ensure fal'Cie subjugation.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Deciding to mount a rescue, they plan to use a PSICOM craft to slip aboard the {Italic}Palamecia{Italic}, flagship of the Sanctum Skyfleet and prison vessel for the captured l'Cie.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Galenth Dysley, Primarch and representative of the people, is also on board. His presence almost certainly signifies a trap, but what other choice do they have?";
"0130║$atar_exp_610p0" = "The ease with which the l'Cie slip aboard the {Italic}Palamecia{Italic} is, as they had anticipated, simply a part of the plan to lure them into a trap.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}They make it onto the Skyfleet flagship with the help of the Cavalry, only to be greeted by a squad of PSICOM soldiers as soon as their feet hit the deck.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}The l'Cie do not back down.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}This is more than just a rescue attempt{Var85 87}it is a battle that could affect the future of Cocoon.";
"0131║$atar_exp_610p1" = "The Primarch heads the forces aboard the {Italic}Palamecia{Italic}. If they can capture Dysley and force him to reveal the fal'Cie's schemes, it may be enough to liberate Cocoon from the Sanctum's tyranny and free the hearts and minds of her people.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}If they can prove how the government has manipulated its citizens into hating Pulse, and change the way people feel, then maybe the l'Cie can find a place in Cocoon's society{Var85 87}and some hope for the future.";
"0132║$atar_exp_620p0" = "Despite being driven to the brink of suicide by the sight of his son turning into crystal, Sazh is still alive. Having been captured by Colonel Nabaat in Nautilus, he and Vanille are now on their way to Eden to be executed.{Text NewLine}The only reason they still live is so they can be murdered in front of an audience.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}When Sazh learned that Vanille was the one responsible for his grief, he was consumed with rage. Now, he listens calmly to her tale:{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Once a l'Cie who fought in the war against Cocoon, Vanille spent centuries in crystal stasis.";
"0133║$atar_exp_620p1" = "When she finally awoke, she found that her companion, Fang, had lost all memory of their previous Focus. Afraid that their new charge would culminate in another horrific battle, Vanille chose to feign memory loss in an attempt to flee from her destiny{Var85 87}a decision which has led to untold tragedy.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Somewhat ironically, hearing Vanille's melancholy tale sparks a flicker of hope in Sazh. If Vanille can emerge from crystal stasis, then maybe Dajh can too.{Text NewLine}{Text 112}Stirred from his despondency by this thought, Sazh helps Vanille to overpower the cell guards and the pair begin their escape.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}But this time, they're not running away from their fate{Var85 87}they're taking charge of it.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Meanwhile, elsewhere on the ship, the other l'Cie battle through waves of enemy soldiers in an attempt to rescue their friends.";
"0134║$atar_exp_630p0" = "Colonel Jihl Nabaat is growing frantic.{Text NewLine}All her carefully laid plans and contingencies are crumbling around her as the seemingly unstoppable l'Cie rampage through the ship. To make matters worse, the airship's main reactor has suddenly shut down. Jihl has yet to grasp what is behind the loss of power...{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Sazh and Vanille are able to retrieve their equipment soon after escaping confinement. At the same time, their companions make good progress as routes open up across the ship. And the sudden engine failure has quieted the wind howling across the deck.";
"0135║$atar_exp_630p1" = "As if guided by fate, the l'Cie are reunited{Var85 87}and their success gives them renewed vigor to attempt the impossible.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}And now, at last, they know what they have to do. They will topple the Sanctum, overturn fal'Cie rule, and put the fate of Cocoon in the hands of the people.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}If they can just make it to the bridge of the {Italic}Palamecia{Italic}, they'll show the Primarch what l'Cie are really capable of...";
"0136║$atar_exp_640p0" = "To the amazement of the l'Cie, the Primarch reveals himself to be a fal'Cie whose true name is Barthandelus. Showing nothing but contempt for his human tools, he proceeds to casually slaughter Colonel Nabaat and her subordinates.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Barthandelus then shrugs off the l'Cie's attacks, and, with mocking laughter, declares his intention to 'enlighten' them.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}In order to fulfill the Focus given to them by the Pulse fal'Cie, he states, one of the l'Cie must become Ragnarok, and bring about the end of Cocoon.";
"0137║$atar_exp_640p1" = "Serah's task was simply to assemble the tools to achieve this end{Var85 87}to bring Snow and the others into contact with the lowerworld being. Her wish that they protect Cocoon was just that{Var85 87}a wish. It had nothing to do with her, or their, Focus.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Confounded by the naked truth, the dumbstruck l'Cie flee the plummeting {Italic}Palamecia{Italic} on an airship provided by Barthandelus. Their craft is guided by an unseen power that protects them from Colonel Rosch's onslaught and flies them towards the 'reality' hidden beneath the capital of Cocoon...";
"0138║$atar_exp_650p0" = "Shortly after their reunion, the l'Cie's newfound conviction is shaken by the fal'Cie masquerading as a human Primarch. If what Barthandelus says is true, then their Focus really is the destruction of Cocoon.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}One of them must become the beast from their vision, and doom the floating world to annihilation by killing the entity that keeps it aloft{Var85 87}the being known as Orphan.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}But does Barthandelus desire the destruction of his own world? Why else would he explain their Focus in such detail?";
"0139║$atar_exp_650p1" = "The l'Cie cannot fathom his true intent, but there is no denying that a power beyond their understanding prevented their demise. Their airship flew with a mind of its own, evading Rosch's attacks, and bringing them to this place{Var85 87}a sprawling relic of Pulse architecture nestled right beneath Eden, the capital city of Cocoon.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Each of them feels lost and confused, but Snow, in particular, seems to have been hit hard.{Text NewLine}{Text 112}Believing Serah's wish to be his Focus is what kept him moving forward all this time. Now that he has learned that she, too, was an enemy of Cocoon, the very foundation of his belief has fallen into ruin...";
"0140║$atar_exp_660p0" = "Fang and Vanille remember a legend from their homeland{Var85 87}a legend about the Arks.{Text NewLine}Arks are supposedly huge armories filled with living weapons, their occupants kept in stasis for the day war comes to Gran Pulse.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}But why is one of them on Cocoon?{Text NewLine}It was probably transported in the same manner as the Vestige in Bodhum, but if it became known that such a facility existed so close to Eden, even the massed ranks of the entire Sanctum army would be powerless to stem the resulting tide of panic.";
"0141║$atar_exp_660p1" = "Could it be that the government has been kept ignorant of the Ark's existence in the event that such a crisis be required?{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}The Arks are also known as training grounds for l'Cie.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}As their brands burn with the awakening of new powers, the companions begin to understand Barthandelus's intention in sending them to this place. The fal'Cie posing as the Primarch really does wish the l'Cie to complete their Focus and bring an end to Cocoon. Why else give them this opportunity to hone their skills?";
"0142║$atar_exp_670p0" = "While exploring the Ark, the l'Cie meet Cid Raines, who reveals the horrendous truth of the fal'Cie's agenda:{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}The divinity responsible for creating both fal'Cie and humans{Var85 87}known only as the 'Maker'{Var85 87}departed long ago, leaving the world to fall into ruin. To save it, the Maker must return, but to call back the Maker, millions of lives{Var85 87}no less than the entire population of Cocoon{Var85 87}must be sacrificed.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Thus the Sanctum fal'Cie carefully nurture the people within their floating shell in preparation for this bloody tribute.";
"0143║$atar_exp_670p1" = "Yet, unable to unmake that which they themselves have made, the fal'Cie have long sought suitable tools to carry out Cocoon's destruction. The Pulse l'Cie, in short, have been surreptitiously watched and protected so that they might gain the strength necessary to complete their terrible Focus...{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Raines, the bearer of this awful truth, reveals himself to be a l'Cie under the control of Barthandelus.{Text NewLine}{Text 112}So far, he has guided Lightning and her friends as his Focus required, but now he chooses to exercise his final shred of free will in an act of rebellion against the fal'Cie{Var85 87}if he can kill the Pulse l'Cie, then Cocoon will escape destruction.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}His last wish as a human is to fight for the survival of his world. Even in defeat, he turns to crystal, and gains his eternal reward.";
"0144║$atar_exp_680p0" = "Seeing Raines turn to crystal, not as a consequence of completing his Focus as a l'Cie, but from fulfilling his wish as a human, has lifted Snow out of his uncharacteristic despair.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}It seems that it doesn't matter what his Focus is. All he needs to do is remember Serah's words, and fight to protect Cocoon just as he originally intended. And ultimately, if ignoring his task were to turn him into a Cie'th, wouldn't that still be better than ignoring his fianc{Var85 200}e's wish and destroying the world?";
"0145║$atar_exp_680p1" = "Snow decides to spend whatever time he has left in a way that would make Serah proud.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Though the others warm to his idea, Fang stands apart. She'll never let herself, let alone her friends, turn Cie'th. Even if it means tearing Cocoon out of the sky, she'll complete their Focus to save them from that fate.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Her spirit in turmoil, Fang feels her inert brand blaze to life, and looks on in stunned amazement as the Eidolon Bahamut is summoned from the skies.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Eidolons 'save' l'Cie who waver in their conviction by ending their indecision with death. Realizing that Bahamut is a danger to all of them, Fang is forced to rethink her path.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Unable to stand by and see her friends hurt, she helps them to defeat the Eidolon and finds a new road has opened up before them.";
"0146║$atar_exp_690p0" = "The fal'Cie hope to restore their world with the help of the Maker, but calling back the lost divinity requires the energy generated by the deaths of millions of people. Now, the beings who built Cocoon as a place to nurture their 'tribute' seek to manipulate Pulse l'Cie in the final stages of their grand scheme.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Lightning and her friends have been monitored and assisted by the fal'Cie from the very beginning. Even their clashes with the military have been carefully orchestrated to ensure their survival.";
"0147║$atar_exp_690p1" = "Countless Sanctum soldiers, unaware of the callous fal'Cie's true objectives, have been thrown into the jaws of the l'Cie in an effort to nurture ever-stronger beasts.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Knowing this, there is no clear path for the l'Cie to take. Ignore their Focus and become Cie'th, or give in to the fal'Cie and condemn millions to death.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Their only hope is to trust their own strength of will. They have to follow Raines's noble example{Var85 87}and Serah's parting wish{Var85 87}by going through with their plan to protect Cocoon.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}More determined than ever after the battle with Bahamut, the l'Cie begin their journey to the untamed world of Gran Pulse.";
"0148║$atar_exp_700p0" = "The l'Cie scour Gran Pulse for some way to overcome their Focus, but even after days of searching the bleak terrain, they discover nothing but crumbling ruins and vicious wildlife. No matter how far they range, there is not another soul to be found.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Did the people of Gran Pulse fall victim to the brutal struggle for survival that dominates every aspect of this unforgiving world? And is the rebirth of this same desolate land the purpose behind the Cocoon fal'Cie's plan to slaughter millions of people?";
"0149║$atar_exp_700p1" = "As time passes and their fruitless expedition drags on, the l'Cie slowly succumb to frustration and despair{Var85 87}their most dangerous enemies.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Emotional extremes can accelerate the progress of a l'Cie brand. If a brand evolves to the final stage, it triggers the transformation into a Cie'th.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}They are all reminded of how little time remains when Hope's brand suddenly advances another step.";
"0150║$atar_exp_710p0" = "Eidolons come to grant a despairing l'Cie the death they crave{Var85 87}or so it is believed. But when the Eidolon Alexander is summoned by Hope's confused anguish, Lightning sees a different reason behind the entity's appearance.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}She comes to believe that the Eidolons appear in order to prevent l'Cie from giving up on themselves. When l'Cie, consumed by despair or rage, are close to losing their path, an Eidolon appears and gives them a life-or-death trial to overcome{Var85 87}thereby forcing them to rethink their decision to surrender.";
"0151║$atar_exp_710p1" = "Through his battle with Alexander, Hope renews his determination to survive and rejoins the others as they set off to the north. That way lies the village of Oerba.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}If they can reach Fang and Vanille's hometown, then maybe they can learn the true story behind the War of Transgression, and find a clue to help them break the shackles of their Focus.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}The l'Cie continue their journey, each playing their part to keep this tiny flame of hope alive.";
"0152║$atar_exp_720p0" = "If they choose not to kill Orphan and bring about Cocoon's destruction, Lightning and her companions will transform into Cie'th. But if they do carry out their Focus, their actions will doom the lives of millions of people.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}In search of a way to escape this impossible choice, the l'Cie travel towards the village of Oerba in the north of Gran Pulse.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}On the endless plains they see beasts and birds aplenty, but not a single person. Could the ruin of this world's civilization have been caused by the War of Transgression, centuries before?";
"0153║$atar_exp_720p1" = "Here, where it all began, Fang finally uncovers the truth that Vanille has so desperately tried to conceal. The l'Cie who became Ragnarok and attacked Cocoon during the war was not her cheerful friend but Fang herself. Not wanting Fang to bear the guilt of the beast's bloody rampage, Vanille chose to take the blame in her stead.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}As if to reprimand her for twisting the truth, the Eidolon Hecatoncheir rises from the earth even as the two friends argue. No matter how painful it may be, l'Cie cannot run from reality forever.";
"0154║$atar_exp_725p0" = "When Vanille awoke from crystal stasis, she sought to deny her Focus{Var85 87}Cocoon's doom{Var85 87}by lying that she, like Fang, had lost her memory. But instead of preventing a catastrophe, she only spurred her friend into reckless action.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Desperate to prevent Vanille from becoming a Cie'th, Fang suggested they attack a Sanctum fal'Cie to kick-start their memories, and the tragic incident at Euride Gorge was the result.";
"0155║$atar_exp_725p1" = "Separated from her friend after their escape, Vanille drifted aimlessly until she happened upon Serah.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Though Snow's fianc{Var85 200}e thought the meeting was their first, Vanille knew exactly who Serah was. She was the girl who had wandered into the Bodhum Vestige only to be turned into a l'Cie{Var85 87}a replacement for the Gran Pulsians who had seemingly abandoned their Focus.{Text NewLine}{Text 112}Feeling crushed by guilt and cruel fate, Vanille would have given up there and then had it not been for Serah's advice that if things seem too much to deal with, you should face them later. If you can just survive, there's always the hope that you can overcome your problems. That hope is what has kept Vanille going until now.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}When she describes this touching interlude to Snow, the kind-hearted hero renews his promise to fulfill his beloved Serah's wish. And Lightning, her anger now a distant memory, means to help him do it.";
"0156║$atar_exp_730p0" = "The home that Fang and Vanille remember is a beautiful place surrounded by flowers and nature.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}But the Oerba that greets them after their long, perilous journey is a wasteland, covered in a layer of fine crystal dust. The hope they had been seeking vanishes like a desert mirage.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Though they have turned their backs on their genocidal Focus, the l'Cie's brands have not stopped advancing, and each passing second brings them closer to the moment of monstrous transformation.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Oerba, their last refuge of hope, is a hollow shell, devoid of life.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}But they must continue on. They must follow the road to its inevitable conclusion.";
"0157║$atar_exp_740p0" = "Callous and calculating, the fal'Cie manipulate their human tools via their emotions.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Taking Serah's form to catch the l'Cie off-balance, Barthandelus predicts the imminent destruction of Cocoon.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}He has revived Raines, now a compliant puppet, and instated him as the Sanctum's new Primarch{Var85 87}a ploy designed to provoke the Cavalry revolutionaries into overthrowing the government in outrage at their former leader's betrayal.";
"0158║$atar_exp_740p1" = "The gloating fal'Cie also means to play on the Pulse-phobia of the populace to turn neighbor against neighbor, transforming Cocoon's streets into a bloodbath.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Worse, Barthandelus then describes how the Cavalry, unnoticed amid the chaos, will infiltrate Eden and fall upon Orphan, not understanding that their actions will bring their world crashing down.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}To prevent this disaster, the l'Cie must return to Cocoon{Var85 87}but isn't that what Barthandelus wanted all along?{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}The fal'Cie could be manipulating them again{Var85 87}attempting to draw them into a situation where they have no choice but to become Ragnarok and slay Orphan.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Leaving them yet another airship, Barthandelus vanishes once again. The choice to return to Cocoon and play a part in her destiny lies firmly in the hands of the l'Cie.";
"0159║$atar_exp_750p0" = "Fang and Vanille visit their home in Oerba for the first time in centuries, seeking a way to free themselves from their l'Cie curse. But what they find is a broken and empty shell of a town, half-buried in a sea of crystal dust.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Meanwhile, Cocoon, the home of their fellow l'Cie, is poised to join the village in oblivion. There, the people stand ready to slaughter each other, their minds twisted by fal'Cie illusions.";
"0160║$atar_exp_750p1" = "{Text NewLine}The l'Cie have no choice but to return and prevent the impending devastation. Even if every man, woman, and child on the floating world regards them as mortal enemies, it is still their home.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}But the shackles of the fal'Cie yet bind their fates...{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}With their Focus haunting their every step, the very act of setting foot on Cocoon might invite disaster. Yet return they must. There is a war to stop, and fal'Cie rule to overthrow.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}In this darkest hour, they must hold fast to hope if they are to protect Cocoon. The time for appealing to long-departed deities, lost loved ones, or lights in the sky is past.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}As the l'Cie fly towards their final destiny, they make the only choice that remains to them{Var85 87}a promise to be true to themselves.";
"0161║$atar_exp_760p0" = "Lightning and her friends return to Cocoon only to be greeted by the sudden appearance of an army of mechanical monsters and gigantic beasts. The fal'Cie have activated the Ark hidden beneath the capital, releasing an army of Pulsian terrors into the city.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}With the army in panicked disarray, the Cavalry seizes its chance. Captain Rygdea leads his troops in an assault on the Sanctum offices, and confronts the new Primarch{Var85 87}his former superior and comrade in arms, Cid Raines.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Raines calmly welcomes his own demise. Revived to serve as Barthandelus's pawn, he nevertheless retains a sliver of the will he possessed as a human. And it is humans who must decide Cocoon's future{Var85 87}not fal'Cie slaves.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}The Cavalry presses on with its plans to slay Orphan, unaware that this effort to save the world will only lead to total destruction. Barthandelus has twisted the Cavalry's desire for freedom to meet his own design.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}The l'Cie must stop the Cavalry from reaching the heart of Eden before it is too late.";
"0162║$atar_exp_760p1" = "";
"0163║$atar_exp_770p0" = "The creatures once held in stasis within the Ark are now rampaging through the streets of Eden, but this merely marks the beginning of Cocoon's collapse into chaos. Once news of the 'Pulse invasion' spreads to a populace already in the grip of panic, the people will be whipped into a frenzy of terror{Var85 87}and the ensuing orgy of violence will tear society apart.";
"0164║$atar_exp_770p1" = "Yet Cocoon may not survive long enough for that to happen. Even now, the members of the Cavalry charge into the heart of the capital, unwittingly seeking to extinguish the source of power that keeps Cocoon aloft: Orphan. Their idealism is being used against them.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Their quest for liberation is just another cog in Barthandelus's scheme to call back the Maker. He will see the world shattered, and offer the lives of its inhabitants in sacrifice.{Text NewLine}{Text 112}Fearing they may already be too late, the l'Cie rush after the Cavalry, through a city engulfed in the flames of war.";
"0165║$atar_exp_780p0" = "No human wishes to see the world destroyed. The l'Cie, the Cavalry, and even the soldiers of the Sanctum army are all fighting to keep Cocoon safe from harm.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}But despite their common goal, they have been forced into conflict by the machinations of the fal'Cie. It is the great error of these 'higher beings' to view humans as mere tools{Var85 87}yet humans are guilty of a similar crime.";
"0166║$atar_exp_780p1" = "Indeed, it is men like PSICOM's Colonel Rosch, and their outright refusal to believe l'Cie can be anything but tools, that now prevents an alliance which could save mankind.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}The l'Cie know that the only way to foil Barthandelus's plan is to protect Orphan. Yet both the Cavalry and Colonel Rosch threaten to thwart them, firmly believing that they alone represent Cocoon's only hope of salvation. If Lightning and the others cannot convince them of the truth, is bloodshed then the only option?{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Suddenly, the NORA crew arrive to lend a hand, and Snow is relieved to find that, in spite of his transformation into a l'Cie, his old friends treat him just as they always had. Their acceptance as much as their assistance gives the l'Cie new hope.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}They can't give up.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}There is still a chance to end this conflict, and save the people from themselves.";
"0167║$atar_exp_790p0" = "When the blinding flash of light fades, where there were soldiers now stand mindless Cie'th. With no Focus to complete, their souls are stripped from them at the instant of their transformation. Thus do the fal'Cie dispose of humans whose usefulness has ended.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Rosch, the sole survivor, defends the Sanctum army and their obedience to fal'Cie law. Even though he harbors doubts as to the fal'Cie's true intentions, the peace and harmony of Cocoon cannot be upheld without them.";
"0168║$atar_exp_790p1" = "It is his desire to protect the stability of society that allows him to commit atrocities such as the Purge. The end justifies the means.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Realizing his error in judgment, the PSICOM director still cannot change what is done. The only remaining path is to live his final moments as he has tried to live his life{Var85 87}in the service of Cocoon.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}The conflict among the people is coming to an end, but the danger to Cocoon is not over.{Text NewLine}Not until Barthandelus and his schemes are defeated.";
"0169║$atar_exp_800p0" = "The Cavalry soldiers set on overthrowing fal'Cie rule now wander the halls of the Sanctum as monstrous Cie'th.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Barthandelus never intended for them to reach Orphan. It was merely a ruse to spur the reluctant l'Cie into action. Though the companions refuse to complete their Focus, he no longer needs to manipulate their minds.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}";
"0170║$atar_exp_800p1" = "All that remains is to crush any hope they have for their future. When that hope turns to despair, one of them, consumed by anger and regret, will transform into Ragnarok.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}And the beast{Var85 87}an unstoppable incarnation of wrath{Var85 87}will slay Orphan. Cocoon will shatter, and the energy released by the deaths of millions will summon the Maker.{Text NewLine}{Text 112}A new dawn approaches...{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}It is for this day that Barthandelus built Cocoon, tended to its people, and watched over the servants of the Pulse fal'Cie. He gives one final order to the fal'Cie Eden: guide the steps of the cursed l'Cie. Bring them to the one who dreams of death.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Bring them to Orphan's Cradle.";
