"0345║$atc_exp_0920p0" = "{Italic}{Text NewLine}Luminous lamented,{Text NewLine}{Var85 96}{Var85 96}{Var85 96}for creation spiraled unto doom.{Text NewLine}Stout fashioned earth,{Text NewLine}{Var85 96}{Var85 96}{Var85 96}that future might take root.{Text NewLine}Sage turned mind's eye inward,{Text NewLine}{Var85 96}{Var85 96}{Var85 96}seeking truth profound.{Text NewLine}Fool desired naught,{Text NewLine}{Var85 96}{Var85 96}{Var85 96}and soon was made one with it.{Text NewLine}Maker forged fal'Cie,{Text NewLine}{Var85 96}{Var85 96}{Var85 96}from fragments Maker's own.{Text NewLine}Maker forged Man,{Text NewLine}{Var85 96}{Var85 96}{Var85 96}from traces once Divine.{Italic}{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}{Italic}In time the gods departed,{Text NewLine}{Var85 96}{Var85 96}{Var85 96}leaving all by their hands wrought.{Text NewLine}Fal'Cie were as Man forsaken,{Text NewLine}{Var85 96}{Var85 96}{Var85 96}orphans of Maker absconded.{Italic}{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}-Author unknown{End}{Question}";
"0346║$atc_exp_0930p0" = "{Italic}And lo, the viper Lindzei bore fangs into the pristine soil of our Gran Pulse; despoiled the land and from it crafted a cocoon both ghastly and unclean.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Lies spilled forth from the serpent's tongue: 'Within this shell lies paradise.' Men heard these lies and were seduced and led away.{Italic}{Text NewLine}{Text 112}{Italic}O cursed are the fools who trust a snake and turn their backs upon the bounty of Pulse's hallowed land! For those who dwell in that cocoon are not Men, but slaves of the demon Lindzei.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Ye who honor Pulse: rise unto the heavens, and cast down the viper's nest!{Italic}{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}-Author unknown{End}{Question}";
"0347║$atc_exp_0940p0" = "{Italic}{Text NewLine}How long now, since the demons of Cocoon violated this land? Where once the peoples of Gran Pulse stood as one, united against a common foe, today we stand divided, at war amongst ourselves.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}We walk on the edge of a knife, teetering, ever but one step from our demise. How tired a species, that we must rob our own of the necessities for life lest we succumb to the fate to which we so willingly subject others!{Italic}{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}{Italic}Even Haeri, at the height of its glory, laid to ruin by a menace greater still! Surely the vipers within that floating nest look down upon us with self-righteous scorn, to see this decline of our once-great civilization.{Italic}{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}-{Italic}Criticisms of a Pulsian People{Italic}{End}{Question}";
"0348║$atc_exp_0950p0" = "{Italic}It was the Great and Hallowed Pulse who, seeking to expand divine domain, parted the chaos and fashioned realm within; made fal'Cie, and charged them with this world's completion.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}The fal'Cie, anxious to please the hand that shaped them, labored devotedly at the task they had been given. They made l'Cie of men so that they, too, might be able to aid the greater cause. Men, in turn, offered praise and prayer to Hallowed Pulse, naming their great land in honor of its architect.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Yet still the architect departed.{Italic}{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}-{Italic}On the Nature of Fal'Cie{Italic}{End}{Question}";
"0349║$atc_exp_0960p0" = "{Italic}Two l'Cie are they, the Chosen, and from the North they hail. Endowed are they with fal'Cie Focus, to bear the burden of the Beast.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}My brothers and sisters of Gran Pulse: Honor the Chosen in your prayers! Let the blade forged of their will be tempered by your faith, that it might sunder that devilish cocoon's facade!{Italic}{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}-{Italic}A Call to Arms{Italic}{End}{Question}";
"0350║$atc_exp_0970p0" = "{Italic}Ragnarok took wing; made to smite Cocoon, and thereby deliver us our everlasting peace. But Her Providence would not let it be.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}The Goddess pitied the fools who so blindly bowed to Lindzei's will, and so She robbed Ragnarok of power, putting the l'Cie to an early crystal sleep, Focus yet incomplete.{Italic}{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}-Sermons of the seeress Paddra Nsu-Yeul{End}{Question}";
"0351║$atc_exp_0980p0" = "{Italic}The fal'Cie of Hallowed Pulse offer us no salvation. Populations dwindle, and still they but make more of us l'Cie, dealing out one incomprehensible Focus after the next as they drive us toward our end.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Men take up arms against their brothers now. We, who should be joining hands to survive in the face of nature's trials, turn on one another to secure what few of her blessings remain.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}I suspect that even the city of Paddra, this last bastion of civilization, will not long stand against the evils we now perpetrate. Human life on Gran Pulse has passed the point of no return.{Italic}{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}-{Italic}Criticisms of a Pulsian People{Italic}{End}{Question}";
"0352║$atc_exp_0990p0" = "{Italic}Her Providence sought nothing.{Text NewLine}Her Providence made nothing.{Text NewLine}She but looked on, silent in Her sorrow.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}The Goddess pitied mortals, destined as they were to die, and so She deigned to intervene in the hour of their greatest peril. She averted cataclysm that was to be, and put to rest the ones who would have robbed so many of what time fate had ordained.{Italic}{Text NewLine}{Text 112}{Italic}Her compassion did not end at this.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}The Goddess pitied also those subjected to that fate of Focus, crueler still than death. To them She sent Her messengers, to deliver hope when all was lost.{Italic}{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}-Sermons of the seeress Paddra Nsu-Yeul{End}{Question}";
"0353║$atc_exp_1000p0" = "{Italic}They say the fal'Cie made the Arks in preparation for battle against the menace that lurks beyond. Where is this 'beyond' of which they speak? Do they mean Cocoon, and the demons that dwell within? If so, they are mistaken. The legends of the Arks date far before that sphere was even crafted; whispers even hint at Arks displaced around the time of Cocoon's creation, spirited away to be hidden in its shell.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}What, then, is the 'menace'? What distant threat confronts us, and to what purpose? The gods vanished from this place. Are they now residents of the 'beyond'?{Italic}{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}-{Italic}On the Nature of Fal'Cie{Italic}{End}{Question}";
"0354║$atc_exp_1010p0" = "{Italic}As our fal'Cie are the children of Hallowed Pulse, so are the fal'Cie who lurk within Cocoon the brood of Lindzei.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}But all gods are not alike.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Lindzei is cunning and false; sovereign to snakes and fiends; an anathema to be abhorred.{Text NewLine}{Text 112}{Text NewLine}Cocoon fal'Cie are of Fell Lindzei's line, yet that did not spare them. They were betrayed all the same; left orphans when their Succubus fled this earthly realm.{Italic}{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}-{Italic}A Call to Arms{Italic}{End}{Question}";
"0355║$atc_exp_1020p0" = "{Italic}We've long held the goal of the fal'Cie's endless excavations to be the expansion of our world's inhabitable space{Var85 87}the creation of new lands with which to honor the gods. But I contend this to be false. Their methods lack the order one would expect if that were their purpose, and what's more, the gods they would honor have long since departed this world.{Italic}{Text NewLine}{Text 112}{Text NewLine}{Italic}I propose a different explanation: the fal'Cie are hunting. Whether they seek a way to recall the gods or to journey to their side I cannot say, but I do believe the fal'Cie seek their lost deities. They search the earth, the skies, the waters, and even the deep places, seeking a gateway to the Divine.{Italic}{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}-{Italic}On the Nature of Fal'Cie{Italic}{End}{Question}";
"0356║$atc_exp_1030p0" = "{Italic}When our earthly vessels meet their end, the souls they housed must leave this world. Would the path of their migration not be the same one taken by our departed gods? Must they not pass through the same doorway the Divine employed to reach that place that lies beyond?{Text NewLine}{Text 112}{Text NewLine}If this is the case, it stands to reason that, should a great many lives at once be cut short, a flood of souls would surge through the aforementioned portal. The Door would be thrown wide, and perhaps we might even glimpse the gleaming light of Divinity beyond.{Italic}{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}-{Italic}On the Nature of Fal'Cie{Italic}{End}{Question}";
"0357║$atc_exp_1040p0" = "{Italic}Children of Hallowed Pulse scour earth, searching substance for the Door. Those of Fell Lindzei harvest souls, combing ether for the same. So have I seen.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}The Door, once shut, was locked away, with despair its secret key; sacrifice, the one hope of seeing it unsealed.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}When the twilight of the gods at last descends upon this world, what emerges from the unseeable expanse beyond that Door will be but music, and that devoid of words: the lamentations of the Goddess Etro, as She sobs Her song of grief.{Italic}{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}-Author unknown{End}{Question}";
