"0462║$atch_exp_000p0" = "This former soldier was a member of the Guardian Corps, Bodhum Security Regiment. Last name: 'Farron.' She is known as 'Lightning,' but her true name is a mystery.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Serah, her only family left in the world, has become a l'Cie. Lightning boards the Purge train in an effort to rescue her sister from the fal'Cie, but Serah turns to crystal right before her eyes. However, it is not long until Lightning herself becomes a fal'Cie servant.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}She has lost her sister, and become a Pulse l'Cie{Var85 87}an enemy of Cocoon. What hope does she have left?";
"0463║$atch_exp_001p0" = "Lightning was formerly a sergeant in the Guardian Corps, Bodhum Security Regiment.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Wanting to outgrow the painful memories of her parents' death, she abandoned her childhood name to take up her current moniker. She retains her family name of 'Farron.'{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Cursed as her sister was with the fate of a l'Cie, Lightning's frustration leads her to declare war against the Sanctum. She eventually sees her actions for what they are: an escape from reality.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Finally accepting Snow for his genuine efforts to save Serah, Lightning now fights a different battle{Var85 87}a battle to overcome her Focus and see her sister return from crystal slumber.";
"0464║$atch_exp_002p0" = "Lightning was formerly a sergeant in the Guardian Corps, Bodhum Security Regiment.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Wanting to outgrow the painful memories of her parents' death, she abandoned her childhood name 'Claire' to take up her current moniker.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Faced with a Focus that demands the destruction of Cocoon, Lightning now refuses the destiny thrust upon her by the fal'Cie, and swears to follow her own will through to the end.{Text NewLine}{Text 112}To save Cocoon as her sister wished, the young woman makes a decision to return to the world that sees her and her companions as dangerous fugitives.";
"0465║$atch_exp_010p0" = "Without a family to take care of him, Snow was raised in a Sanctum facility. Now he leads the rebellious group of youths known as NORA.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}To prevent his beloved Serah from becoming a Cie'th, he swears to help her fulfill her Focus. However, before they discover what that Focus is, Serah falls into crystal slumber.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Now a l'Cie himself, Snow interprets his fianc{Var85 200}e's last words as the task he must complete{Var85 87}saving Cocoon.";
"0466║$atch_exp_011p0" = "Without a family to take care of him, Snow was raised in a Sanctum facility. Now he leads the rebellious group of youths known as NORA.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Believing Serah's last words to be his Focus, Snow pours all of his energy into saving Cocoon. His fervor is blunted by the claim that she was nothing more than a fal'Cie tool, but he renews his determination to overcome the destiny laid before them. Nothing will prevent him from protecting his world and seeing Serah return from her crystallized state.";
"0467║$atch_exp_020p0" = "Sazh is a trained civilian airship pilot.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Though all of Cocoon's people view Pulse beings as invaders to be repulsed, few outside of the military decide to take matters into their own hands. What drives Sazh{Var85 87}an ordinary citizen{Var85 87}to attack the Pulse fal'Cie in the Hanging Edge?{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}After joining Lightning in her battle against the lowerworld entity, Sazh shares her fate in becoming a l'Cie.";
"0468║$atch_exp_021p0" = "A trained civilian airship pilot, Sazh has been raising his son alone since the untimely passing of his wife almost three years ago. His son, Dajh, became a Sanctum l'Cie during the Euride Gorge incident. Without a clear Focus, the little boy will eventually turn into a monstrous Cie'th.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Guessing that Dajh's task could be to destroy beings from Pulse, Sazh boards the Purge train as part of a plan to take care of the fal'Cie himself. His self-appointed mission ends with him becoming a Pulse l'Cie{Var85 87}an existence that puts him into conflict with his son's status as a Sanctum servant.";
"0469║$atch_exp_022p0" = "A trained civilian airship pilot, Sazh has been raising his son alone since the untimely passing of his wife almost three years ago.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}A Sanctum l'Cie in the custody of PSICOM, Dajh turns to crystal the moment he is reunited with his father. Yet even after later discovering Vanille is responsible for his son's misfortune, Sazh is unable to bring himself to shoot her.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}His goal now is to survive the coming conflict with the hope that his son will one day wake from his crystal stasis.";
"0470║$atch_exp_030p0" = "Hope is a boy who, along with his mother, becomes a victim of the Purge.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Answering Snow's call for volunteers, Hope's mother joins the rebellion, but is killed in the subsequent conflict. From that moment onwards, the grief-stricken teen harbors a consuming hatred for the NORA leader.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}With Vanille's encouragement, Hope follows Snow into the Pulse Vestige. Within those ancient chambers, they encounter the fal'Cie and are cursed with the brands of l'Cie.";
"0471║$atch_exp_031p0" = "Hope lives in the city of Palumpolum. However, when he visits the town of Bodhum with his mother, Nora, they are swept away by the chaos of the Purge. Nora dies in the ensuing violence, and Hope later becomes a Pulse l'Cie.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}The boy blames Snow for his mother's death. Driven by his desire for revenge against the NORA leader and the Sanctum, Hope eagerly joins Lightning on her headlong charge into battle.";
"0472║$atch_exp_032p0" = "An incidental victim of the Purge, Hope survives the ensuing violence only to become a l'Cie. Blaming Snow for his mother's death during the fighting, the boy gives a name to his revenge: Operation Nora.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Hope eventually realizes that his rage is simply a crutch to help him through his grief, and decides he needs a real reason to keep on going.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}He mends his relationship with his father, and sets off on a journey to discover a way to escape his destiny as a l'Cie.";
"0473║$atch_exp_040p0" = "Vanille is a young woman who was also aboard the Purge train. Irrepressibly cheerful, she seems unaffected by the desperate situation around her.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}After being rescued from the train by Snow and his band of rebels, Vanille ends up sitting next to Hope and his mother.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Following his mother's death, she sees the way the boy glares at the NORA leader. Vanille encourages Hope to join her and enter the Pulse Vestige, where they encounter the lowerworld fal'Cie.";
"0474║$atch_exp_041p0" = "Pretending to be branded at the same time as the rest of her companions, Vanille actually became a l'Cie on Gran Pulse long ago.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Hundreds of years in the past, she and Fang completed their Focus and turned to crystal. Upon waking, they seemed to have lost all memory of those events, and had no knowledge of their present task.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}While trying to prevent Vanille from becoming a Cie'th, Fang caused the incident at Euride Gorge{Var85 87}the event that turned Dajh into a Sanctum l'Cie.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Parted from her friend, Vanille wandered Cocoon alone until the day of the Purge.";
"0475║$atch_exp_042p0" = "Vanille is a l'Cie who was born on Gran Pulse.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Several hundred years ago, both she and Fang entered crystal stasis. While they slumbered, the entire structure housing them and the fal'Cie was transported to Cocoon.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}After they awake and she learns that Fang is missing memories, Vanille lies and says she has forgotten her Focus as well. She wants to escape from a fate that could lead to more suffering for everyone, but her twisting of the truth has the opposite effect: it leads Fang into rash actions that have devastating consequences for both Dajh and Serah.";
"0476║$atch_exp_043p0" = "Vanille is a l'Cie who was born on Gran Pulse.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Given a Focus to destroy Cocoon, she became Ragnarok and scarred the floating world's shell. Though the battle was lost, both Vanille and Fang were 'rewarded' with a centuries-long crystal stasis.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}After waking on Cocoon, Vanille pretends to have forgotten her Focus. She is prepared to let herself become a Cie'th to prevent any more suffering, but her actions, or lack thereof, end up twisting the fates of all those around her.";
"0477║$atch_exp_044p0" = "Vanille is a l'Cie who was born on Gran Pulse. Her full name stands for 'Vanille of the Dia clan, from the village of Oerba.'{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Along with Fang, she was given a Focus to destroy Cocoon. Fang was the one who became Ragnarok and attacked the floating world several centuries in the past, but Vanille lies about this and her other memories.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}After meeting with Serah, an innocent victim of the Gran Pulsian's lies, Vanille decides she will do nothing else to harm Cocoon and resigns herself to becoming a Cie'th.";
"0478║$atch_exp_050p0" = "A mysterious woman captures Snow on Lake Bresha after his exhausting battle with PSICOM and the Twin Sisters. She bears the mark of a l'Cie, but her brand appears scorched and twisted.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}As a servant of Pulse she should be fleeing the Sanctum army, but she seems to be working with one of the military's units.";
"0479║$atch_exp_051p0" = "Fang is a l'Cie who was born on Gran Pulse, the world that stretches out below floating shell of Cocoon.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}She joined Vanille in a centuries-long crystal stasis, but awoke with no memories of her Focus or what she did to complete it.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}To prevent Vanille's transformation into a Cie'th, Fang tries to recapture memories of their task but in doing so, causes the incident at Euride Gorge.{Text NewLine}{Text 112}Separated from her friend, the proud warrior-woman finds herself working with Raines and the Cavalry he leads as they track down l'Cie.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Fang's brand is scorched and twisted, its progress halted.";
"0480║$atch_exp_052p0" = "Fang is a l'Cie who was born on Gran Pulse. Her full name stands for 'Fang of the Yun clan, from the village of Oerba.'{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Centuries ago, she and Vanille were given a Focus to destroy Cocoon. Fang became Ragnarok and cracked Cocoon's shell, but they were both turned to crystal before their task was complete. The Vestige in which they slumbered was lifted by a fal'Cie onto the very world they tried to shatter. Waking years later, Fang's brand{Var85 87}as well as the memory of her Focus{Var85 87}is now obscured and indistinct.";
"0481║$atch_exp_060p0" = "Serah is Lightning's younger sister. Despite losing both of her parents, she lives happily enough with her older sibling. Serah's only real concern is Lightning's disapproval of her boyfriend, Snow.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}However, that all changes when she encounters the fal'Cie Anima and is branded as a Pulse l'Cie. {Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Without ever uncovering her task, she urges the others to save Cocoon before suddenly turning to crystal. Though he cannot know for sure, Snow believes her final words to be the Focus they must complete.";
"0482║$atch_exp_061p0" = "Serah is Lightning's younger sister and Snow's fianc{Var85 200}e.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Also a Pulse l'Cie, she has gained eternal life and slumbers in crystal stasis. Snow believes their Focus is to save the world as Serah wished, but Barthandelus explains that her task was simply to gather the tools for Cocoon's destruction.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Was Serah nothing more than a pawn{Var85 87}an unwitting enemy of Cocoon?";
"0483║$atch_exp_070p0" = "Dajh is a boy who loves his father{Var85 87}and chocobos!{Var85 87}unconditionally. Though his mother passed away three years ago, he remains a cheerful and energetic child.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}When Sazh lets him out of his sight for a moment during a trip to the energy plant, Dajh is caught up in a Pulse incident that leaves him a Sanctum l'Cie.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Now with the ability to sense power of Pulse origin, the little boy involuntarily discovers the fal'Cie in the Bodhum Vestige. With his Focus still unknown, Dajh faces eventual transformation into a Cie'th.";
"0484║$atch_exp_071p0" = "Dajh is Sazh's only child. His mother passed away three years ago, but instead of being miserable, he bravely comforts his grieving father.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}During the incident at the Euride Gorge energy plant, Dajh is made into a Sanctum l'Cie with the ability to sense power of Pulse origin. Although he discovers the fal'Cie in Bodhum, his true Focus{Var85 87}capturing Pulse l'Cie{Var85 87}is learned when he is reunited with his father and turns to crystal.";
"0485║$atch_exp_080p0" = "Nora is Hope's mother.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Worried about the worsening relationship between her son and his father, Nora wonders how to break down the barriers Hope has created.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Wanting to protect her boy from the horrors of the Purge, she volunteers to join the battle, but is killed during the chaotic conflict.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Nora begs Snow to get Hope home, but the NORA leader never hears the boy's name before she slips from his grasp.";
"0486║$atch_exp_090p0" = "Bartholomew is Hope's father.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}He loves both his wife and son, but is clumsy at expressing it. Things are made even more difficult by Hope's rebellious age and unreasoning resentment towards his dad.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Bartholomew has spent his days sick with worry, ever since Hope and Nora were caught up in the middle of the Purge.";
"0487║$atch_exp_091p0" = "Bartholomew is Hope's father, but has difficulties relating to his teenage son.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Though deeply upset by his wife's death, he sees how much Hope has grown during the subsequent events, and encourages him to find his own path and make his own decisions.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Now wanted by the Sanctum for his actions in aiding Pulse l'Cie, Bartholomew is currently under the protection of the Cavalry.";
"0488║$atch_exp_100p0" = "Galenth Dysley is the Primarch{Var85 87}the human representative of the Sanctum. Acting as a bridge between the fal'Cie Eden and a citizen-elected council, he facilitates the government of Cocoon.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Until now, he has been seen as a conservative leader, never forcing the direction of the council, and always having the best interests of the people at heart. But with the discovery of the Pulse fal'Cie in Bodhum, his leadership becomes ruthless and oppressive, with the Purge policy being instigated over the span of a single night.";
"0489║$atch_exp_110p0" = "Acting in the guise of a human Primarch, Galenth Dysley has concealed his true identity as the fal'Cie Barthandelus.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}He reveals to Lightning and her companions that their Focus is for one of them to take on the form of Ragnarok and shatter Cocoon.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Despite overseeing Cocoon's prosperity for so long, it seems he now desires its destruction. To that end, he has watched over the fugitive l'Cie, and even taken a direct hand in their survival.";
"0490║$atch_exp_120p0" = "Cid Raines is the commander of the Wide-area Response Brigade, a military unit otherwise known as the 'Cavalry.' While lacking the sheer firepower of PSICOM, the Cavalry is considered one of the most elite groups within the Guardian Corps.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}As a brigadier general in the Sanctum army, Raines should stand ready to repel the forces of Pulse. However, he seems to be seeking out the fugitive l'Cie and taking them captive to some end that remains to be seen.";
"0491║$atch_exp_121p0" = "Cid Raines is the commander of the Wide-area Response Brigade, a military unit otherwise known as the 'Cavalry.'{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}His vaunted position in the army has afforded him an unobstructed view of the blind obedience the government shows to the fal'Cie. In order to free Cocoon from the tyranny of these powerful entities, Raines has begun enlisting the assistance of Fang and the other Pulse l'Cie.";
"0492║$atch_exp_122p0" = "Raines had been planning to overthrow fal'Cie rule, but was made into a l'Cie by Barthandelus before those plans could be put into action.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Since then, he has been a part of the fal'Cie's scheme to guide Lightning and the others through their battles with the Sanctum, and along the path to Cocoon's destruction.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}However, Raines regains the will he once had as a human, and attempts to foil Barthandelus's plans by killing the l'Cie. Despite his eventual defeat, the Cavalry commander transforms into crystal.";
"0493║$atch_exp_123p0" = "During his failed attempt to overthrow fal'Cie rule, Cid Raines was cursed to become a pawn of Barthandelus. Concealing his l'Cie status as he continues to lead the Cavalry, Raines pursues his Focus of supporting and guiding Lightning and her companions along the path to Cocoon's destruction.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}After defying his Focus and falling in battle against the fugitive l'Cie, Raines turns to crystal. He is later revived by Barthandelus to serve as the new Primarch{Var85 87}a puppet with the sole purpose of inciting conflict among the people of Cocoon.";
"0494║$atch_exp_130p0" = "Yaag Rosch is a PSICOM officer who graduated with results second only to his fellow trainee, Jihl Nabaat. After proving his leadership in joint missions with the Guardian Corps, his extensive battle experience earned him an early promotion to the rank of colonel.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Assigned command of the anti-l'Cie operations in Palumpolum, Rosch ignores branch rivalries when he requests Guardian Corps cooperation. His only concern is maximizing their efforts to eliminate the l'Cie.";
"0495║$atch_exp_131p0" = "Yaag Rosch is a PSICOM officer who graduated with results second only to his fellow trainee, Jihl Nabaat.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}His leadership skills shown in joint missions with the Guardian Corps earn him the command of the anti-l'Cie operations in Palumpolum.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Despite feeling doubt over the fate of innocents during the Purge, Rosch views the brutal and thankless task of maintaining the overall stability of society to be a soldier's sworn duty.";
"0496║$atch_exp_140p0" = "Jihl Nabaat is a PSICOM officer who graduated at the head of her class, and attained the rank of colonel with unprecedented speed.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}As the supervisor in charge of the investigation at Euride Gorge, as well as Dajh's testing after the boy became a Sanctum l'Cie, Jihl is well acquainted with Sazh. She lent an ear to the distraught father, and listened to all his fears and doubts.";
"0497║$atch_exp_141p0" = "Jihl Nabaat is a talented PSICOM officer who graduated at the head of her class.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}As the supervisor in charge of Dajh's testing, she grew close to his father, Sazh. However, her kindness was simply a ruse to gain access to the boy's l'Cie ability to sense Pulse entities.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}She captures Sazh and Vanille in Nautilus, using them as bait in her scheme to draw the other Pulse l'Cie out of hiding. Jihl's plans backfire when her carefully laid ambush is unable to contain the l'Cie, and Barthandelus disposes of her as he would any other tool.";
"0498║$atch_exp_150p0" = "Rygdea is an officer in the Wide-area Response Brigade led by Cid Raines. Hidden behind his cowboy antics is a man of unwavering courage and integrity.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Disgusted by the deception of the Sanctum, he once thought to retire from the military, but was instead convinced by Raines to join the Cavalry. Finding that the brigadier general shared his ideals, Rygdea now works as his right-hand man in various operations designed to undermine the government's power.";
"0499║$atch_exp_151p0" = "Rygdea is an officer in the Wide-area Response Brigade formerly led by Cid Raines.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Disgusted by the deception of the Sanctum, he thought to retire from the military, but instead joined Raines and the Cavalry in their efforts to bring down the government. Rygdea followed the general without question, unaware of his superior's status as a servant of the Sanctum fal'Cie.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Barthandelus has now placed Raines in the position of Primarch, leaving Rygdea to lead the Cavalry in a charge to topple the Sanctum and destroy Orphan.";
"0500║$atch_exp_160p0" = "Amodar is a lieutenant in the Bodhum Security Regiment, and was Lightning's direct superior.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Climbing his way through the ranks with persistence and hard work, he is respected by his subordinates for his fair treatment on and off the field of battle.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}NORA's unregulated monster-hunting falls under his jurisdiction, but aside from a few warnings for the sake of formality, he generally turns a blind eye to the group's earnest efforts.";
"0501║$atch_exp_170p0" = "A childhood friend of Snow, Gadot is one of the founding members of NORA. With his impressive frame, he sees himself as the group's shock trooper.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Raised almost like a brother to Snow in a Sanctum facility, he knows the NORA leader better than anyone. Despite his often blunt comments and rough behavior, he is devoted to Snow's ideals of compassion.";
"0502║$atch_exp_180p0" = "Friends with Snow from a young age, Lebreau is one of the founding members of NORA. She runs the caf{Var85 200} they opened to fund NORA's operations, and her cooking is one of the{Text NewLine}best-kept secrets in Bodhum.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}With her brusque, no-nonsense manner, the young woman is treated just like one of the guys, and she would have it no other way.";
"0503║$atch_exp_190p0" = "Maqui joined the ranks of NORA out of his admiration for Snow. He loves to tinker with machinery and serves as the group's mechanic. His talent for taking junk and using it to upgrade machines has provided NORA with a secret source of income.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}One day Maqui wants to be a reliable, heroic type like Snow, but he still has a long way to go.";
"0504║$atch_exp_200p0" = "A junior member of NORA, Yuj is a kind-hearted young man with an insatiable interest in fashion.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Though he lacks the same courage as Snow and Gadot in dangerous situations, his calming influence makes him an invaluable asset to the group.";
"0505║$atch_exp_210p0" = "This chocobo chick travels in Sazh's hair. Though it has only been with Sazh for a short while, a strong bond has formed between them.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}The chick has no name, as voicing the true identity of the animal might trigger ripples of destiny across Cocoon and cause a hurricane in Eden. Either that, or Sazh just hasn't thought of one yet.";
"0506║$atch_exp_211p0" = "Sazh purchased this chocobo chick at a stall in Euride Gorge for his son, Dajh. However, while his attention was on the transaction, Dajh ran into the energy plant and headlong into the incident that changed him into a Sanctum l'Cie.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Though boy and chick have met only once during the brief visit Sazh was allowed by PSICOM in Bodhum, they became fast friends. Dajh is trying to decide on what he wants to call the chick, but for now, the chocobo remains nameless.";
