"0552║$m_bttp_00_p0" = "Characters perform abilities in battle by expending segments of the {Color Gold}ATB gauge{Color SkyBlue}, which charges continuously over time.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}{Color Gold}Auto-battle{Color SkyBlue} and other similar commands queue up a set of abilities automatically,{Text NewLine}only requiring you to choose a target.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}The {Color Gold}Abilities{Color SkyBlue} command, on the other hand, allows you to specify individual abilities as you see fit. The number to the right of each ability's name is its ATB cost{Var85 87}the number of charged segments required to perform that action. If you add an ability to the queue by mistake, cancel it with {Key Circle}.{Text NewLine}{End}{Question}";
"0553║$m_bttp_00_p1" = "By pressing {Key Right} at the {Color Gold}Abilities{Color SkyBlue} command, you can select {Color Gold}Repeat{Color SkyBlue}, which queues up the last set of abilities used.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Pressing {Key Triangle} executes a partial command queue. Queue up a single ability and press {Key Triangle} to execute it immediately, or press {Key Triangle} after entering a full queue to act before your ATB gauge has filled. Abilities corresponding to charged segments will be performed, and the rest will be canceled.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Item use does not deplete the ATB gauge, but permanently consumes the item.{End}{Question}";
"0554║$m_bttp_00_p2" = "If the battle team leader's HP reaches zero, the game is over{Var85 87}regardless of whether or not other members are still standing. Always keep a close eye on your leader's HP.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Once you have entered a battle, there is no way to flee. Appraise enemies carefully beforehand. If they appear too powerful, it may be best to avoid the fight entirely.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}You can, however, press {Key Select} after pausing a battle with {Key Start} to select {Color Gold}Retry{Color SkyBlue}, which will return you to a moment just before the battle. Items will be returned, but all damage to enemies will be reset.{End}{Question}";
"0555║$m_bttp_00_t" = "Battle Basics{End}{Question}";
"0556║$m_bttp_01_p0" = "Each time you land a successful attack on an enemy, the enemy's chain gauge{Var85 87}displayed in the upper right corner of the screen{Var85 87}will charge slightly. This gauge drains slowly over time, but by maintaining a steady flow of attacks you can drive the {Color Gold}chain bonus{Color SkyBlue} (the percentage of damage dealt by each attack) upward.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Deliver enough hits in rapid succession, and the gauge will eventually fill. If you connect once more with an enemy in this state, you will {Color Gold}stagger{Color SkyBlue} that enemy. Staggered enemies take a great deal of damage from every attack.{End}{Question}";
"0557║$m_bttp_01_p1" = "Increased damage is not the only effect of staggering a foe. Some abilities behave differently against staggered targets.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Note that some enemies are more easily staggered than others. The chain gauge for easily staggered opponents will charge significantly even as the result of a minor attack.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}It is always to your advantage to stagger enemies quickly, so keep a close eye on their chain gauges and try to maintain a high rate of attacks in order to keep chain bonuses as high as possible.{End}{Question}";
"0558║$m_bttp_01_t" = "Chains and Staggering{End}{Question}";
"0559║$m_bttp_02_p0" = "Each character fights using one of six different {Color Gold}roles{Color SkyBlue}. Changing a character's role changes his or her abilities, and also the way in which that character behaves during combat.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Combinations of role assignments for your battle team are known as {Color Gold}paradigms{Color SkyBlue}. You can create and edit paradigms by pressing {Key Triangle} to open the main menu, and then selecting {Color Gold}Paradigms{Color SkyBlue}.{End}{Question}";
"0560║$m_bttp_02_p1" = "During battle, you can change the team's paradigm at any time. Press {Key L1} to open your paradigm deck, then select a paradigm and press {Key Cross} to perform a {Color Gold}paradigm shift{Color SkyBlue}.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Good combat strategy means keeping a careful eye on your situation and shifting paradigms accordingly. When facing strong enemies, use a paradigm featuring a {Color SandOrange}Sentinel{Color SkyBlue}. Once you've thinned their numbers a bit, shift to a paradigm featuring {Color Rose}Commandos{Color SkyBlue} or {Color Purple}Ravagers{Color SkyBlue} to finish them off more quickly. When things look grim, call in the {Color WhiteGreen}Medics{Color SkyBlue}.{Text NewLine}{End}{Question}";
"0561║$m_bttp_02_t" = "Paradigms{End}{Question}";
"0562║$m_bttp_03_p0" = "{Color Rose}Commandos{Color SkyBlue} are offensive specialists, employing brutal physical attacks and damaging magic as the tools of their trade. Enemy chain gauges drain less rapidly when charged by Commando attacks than when charged by those of other roles.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Commandos are at their most effective when working in tandem with {Color Purple}Ravagers{Color SkyBlue}, who drive chain bonuses upward, thereby increasing the damage dealt to enemies.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Role Bonus: {Color Gold}Augmented Attacks{Color SkyBlue}{Text NewLine}{Italic}{Color Green}Physical and magical attacks deal extra damage. Allies share a reduced bonus.{Color SkyBlue}{Italic}{End}{Question}";
"0563║$m_bttp_03_t" = "Role: Commando{End}{Question}";
"0564║$m_bttp_04_p0" = "{Color Purple}Ravagers{Color SkyBlue} wield powerful magic spells, dealing damage of fire, ice, lightning, water, and other elemental affinities. Combining different abilities allows them to boost enemy chain bonuses significantly, increasing the damage dealt by subsequent attacks. Striking at enemies' elemental weaknesses will further boost chain bonuses.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Role Bonus: {Color Gold}Improved Chaining{Color SkyBlue}{Text NewLine}{Italic}{Color Green}Attacks impact chain bonuses more severely. Allies share a reduced bonus.{Color SkyBlue}{Italic}{End}{Question}";
"0565║$m_bttp_04_t" = "Role: Ravager{End}{Question}";
"0566║$m_bttp_05_p0" = "{Color SandOrange}Sentinels{Color SkyBlue} are defensive specialists. They provide interference, drawing enemy aggression toward themselves and using their enhanced defense to minimize damage to the party. Sentinels have access to the {Color Gold}Provoke{Color SkyBlue} ability, which extends the duration of enemy chain bonuses. They can also use counterattack abilities, which allow them to retaliate when attacked.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Role Bonus: {Color Gold}Damage Reduction{Color SkyBlue}{Text NewLine}{Italic}{Color Green}Physical and magic resistance are increased. Allies share a reduced bonus.{Color SkyBlue}{Italic}{End}{Question}";
"0567║$m_bttp_05_t" = "Role: Sentinel{End}{Question}";
"0568║$m_bttp_06_p0" = "{Color WhiteGreen}Medics{Color SkyBlue} are healers, capable of restoring HP, removing status ailments, and even reviving KO'd allies. When they remove status ailments, the most recently inflicted ailment is always removed first.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Medics are incredibly helpful, but they also reduce a battle team's damage-dealing capacity. If you wish to end battles quickly, it may be necessary to fight without them.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Role Bonus: {Color Gold}Augmented Healing{Color SkyBlue}{Text NewLine}{Italic}{Color Green}Healing abilities and items restore more HP. Allies share a reduced bonus.{Color SkyBlue}{Italic}{End}{Question}";
"0569║$m_bttp_06_t" = "Role: Medic{End}{Question}";
"0570║$m_bttp_07_p0" = "{Color WhitePurple}Synergists{Color SkyBlue} employ a wide range of abilities to enhance their allies' effectiveness in combat. Enhancements range from defensive bonuses to increased damage and the ability to deal elemental damage via normal attacks.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}When facing a particularly powerful enemy, it is a good idea to enter the battle using a paradigm that includes a Synergist. Once enhancements are in place, you can always shift to a different paradigm.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Role Bonus: {Color Gold}Extended Enhancements{Color SkyBlue}{Text NewLine}{Italic}{Color Green}Abilities grant longer-lasting status enhancements. Allies share a reduced bonus.{Color SkyBlue}{Italic}{End}{Question}";
"0571║$m_bttp_07_t" = "Role: Synergist{End}{Question}";
"0572║$m_bttp_08_p0" = "{Color WhiteGray}Saboteurs{Color SkyBlue} use their skills to weaken enemies. Their bag of tricks includes not only attribute-lowering abilities, but also those that inflict status ailments, like {Color Gold}Poison{Color SkyBlue}. When successful, these abilities increase enemy chain bonuses.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Even if they fail to inflict status ailments, Saboteur abilities still deal damage. However, once enemies have been weakened sufficiently, it is generally best to shift Saboteurs to other roles.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Role Bonus: {Color Gold}Boosted Success Rates{Color SkyBlue}{Text NewLine}{Italic}{Color Green}Abilities are more likely to succeed on enemies. Allies share a reduced bonus.{Color SkyBlue}{Italic}{End}{Question}";
"0573║$m_bttp_08_t" = "Role: Saboteur{End}{Question}";
"0574║$m_bttp_09_p0" = "{Color Gold}Techniques{Color SkyBlue} are special abilities you can perform by spending {Color Gold}technical points{Color SkyBlue} (TP). They do not require any ATB gauge expenditure.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}You can perform techniques in battle by selecting the {Color Gold}Techniques{Color SkyBlue} command and then choosing the desired ability. To replenish your TP supply, unleash successful ability queues or earn high ratings after battle. Certain items also restore TP.{End}{Question}";
"0575║$m_bttp_09_p1" = "{Color Gold}Libra{Color SkyBlue} reveals vital information about your enemies. After revealing enemy weaknesses with this technique, your allies will do their best to take advantage of this intel when deciding their actions.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}To view the information you have gathered on enemies, press {Key R1} during battle, or press {Key Triangle} to open the main menu outside of battle and then select {Color Gold}Datalog{Color SkyBlue} followed by {Color Gold}Enemy Intel{Color SkyBlue}. A check mark icon ({Icon Ok}) will be shown by the name of any enemy whose attributes you have fully discerned.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Using Libra does not change enemy strengths or weaknesses. Even if you do not know an enemy's elemental vulnerabilities, using attacks of those elements will be just as effective.{End}{Question}";
"0576║$m_bttp_09_t" = "Libra and Other Techniques{End}{Question}";
"0577║$m_bttp_10_p0" = "When battling Eidolons, it is possible to deal damage to them as you would to any other enemy. However, this alone will not end the battle.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}As you attack Eidolons, a special gauge fills. When this gauge becomes full, you must press {Key Square} to assert your dominance over the Eidolon and claim victory.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Attacking is not the only way to charge the gauge. There are other methods, differing between Eidolons, which are just as effective. Experiment with a variety of abilities to see which work.{End}{Question}";
"0578║$m_bttp_10_t" = "Eidolon Battles{End}{Question}";
"0579║$m_bttp_11_p0" = "A character who has overcome the challenge of an Eidolon learns the {Color Gold}Summon{Color SkyBlue} technique. Performing this technique calls the Eidolon to the summoner's side, where it will attack enemies and restore HP to allies.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}A summoned Eidolon will continue fighting for the party until its SP gauge is empty. The SP gauge drains slowly over time, and also whenever the Eidolon takes damage.{End}{Question}";
"0580║$m_bttp_11_p1" = "After summoning an Eidolon, you can press {Key Square} to activate {Color Gold}gestalt mode{Color SkyBlue} at any time. The level of the Eidolon's {Color Gold}gestalt gauge{Color SkyBlue} determines how long you can remain in this mode.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}The gauge is charged by working with the Eidolon to build attack chains against enemies, so the longer you fight together before activating gestalt mode, the longer you will be able to maintain it.{Text NewLine}{Text 112}In gestalt mode, you can perform various devastating attacks by pressing the buttons indicated on the screen. Alternatively, you can press {Key Cross} to use {Color Gold}Autogestalt{Color SkyBlue}, leaving the choice to your Eidolon. Each ability expends a certain number of time units, shown next to the ability's name, thereby reducing the overall duration of gestalt mode.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Once time runs out, the Eidolon will be dismissed. Enemy chain gauges will be reset and staggered enemies will recover, but the Eidolon will restore your entire battle team's HP and remove any status ailments from members before departing.{End}{Question}";
"0581║$m_bttp_11_t" = "Summoning Eidolons{End}{Question}";
"0582║$m_bttp_12_p0" = "The speed with which you complete a battle determines your {Color Gold}rating{Color SkyBlue}. Ratings influence rewards, such as the spoils obtained after battle.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}For each second you undercut the target time, your score increases by the battle's {Color Gold}PPS{Color SkyBlue} (Points Per Second) value. This score, in turn, determines your rating. Finishing at the target time will earn you an average rating of three stars, out of a maximum of five.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Initiating combat with a preemptive strike provides an {Color Gold}initiative bonus{Color SkyBlue}, pre-applied as an extension of the target time.{End}{Question}";
"0583║$m_bttp_12_t" = "Battle Results{End}{Question}";
"0584║$m_bttp_13_p0" = "Open the main menu by pressing {Key Triangle} and then select {Color Gold}Equipment{Color SkyBlue}, and you will see a list of {Color Gold}passive abilities{Color SkyBlue} along the right side of the screen. These are bonuses granted by equipped weapons and accessories.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Certain combinations of equipment grant additional hidden bonuses that none of the items provide when equipped individually. These are known as {Color Gold}synthesized abilities{Color SkyBlue}, and are identifiable by a special icon ({Icon FilledCirlces}).{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Experiment with a variety of gear to discover which combinations produce the most beneficial results.{End}{Question}";
"0585║$m_bttp_13_t" = "Synthesized Abilities{End}{Question}";
"0586║$m_bttp_14_p0" = "When you wish to develop characters and teach them new abilities, open the main menu with {Key Triangle} and access the {Color Gold}Crystarium{Color SkyBlue}.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}By spending the {Color Gold}crystogen points (CP){Color SkyBlue} that you earn from fighting, you can advance characters' paths of {Color Gold}crystogenesis{Color SkyBlue}, obtaining new crystals that provide a variety of enhancements.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}After selecting {Color Gold}Crystarium{Color SkyBlue} from the main menu, select a character and then press {Key Cross}.{End}{Question}";
"0587║$m_bttp_14_p1" = "Character development paths are divided between the different roles.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}First, select the role in which you would like to develop the chosen character and press {Key Cross} to confirm. The finger cursor will jump to the last crystal obtained for that role.{End}{Question}";
"0588║$m_bttp_14_p2" = "Next, press and hold {Key Cross} and the path of crystogenesis will advance automatically, consuming the CP necessary to do so.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}As the glowing line passes through new crystals, the character will obtain their benefits, such as improved attributes or new abilities. When the character runs out of CP, crystogenesis will grind to a halt.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Characters earn CP at the end of every battle. If you wish to develop them further, fight more enemies, and then return to the Crystarium to spend the CP earned.{End}{Question}";
"0589║$m_bttp_14_p3" = "Abilities learned along each path are role-specific and cannot be shared. For example, learning {Color Gold}Ruin{Color SkyBlue} for the Commando role will not allow a character to use {Color Gold}Ruin{Color SkyBlue} as a Ravager. Techniques are the exception to this rule, and can be used in any role once learned. Boosts to attributes like Strength, Magic, and HP also apply across roles.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Gaining levels in a role increases the effect of that role's bonus. Consider whether you would rather focus on a single role for each character, gaining faster access to powerful abilities, or spread development evenly across multiple roles for flexibility.{End}{Question}";
"0590║$m_bttp_14_t" = "The Crystarium - Part 1{End}{Question}";
"0591║$m_bttp_15_p0" = "You can normally perform crystogenesis until running out of CP, simply by pressing and holding {Key Cross}. However, the process will stop upon reaching points where the path branches. Here, you must press {Key 96} while holding {Key Cross} to choose a direction in which to proceed.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}By pressing {Key 96} without holding {Key Cross}, you can explore various routes to see what crystals lie along them. {Key Select} changes which crystal names are displayed, cycling between only names near the cursor, all names, and none. Pressing {Key L1} or {Key R1} will allow you to develop a different character.{End}{Question}";
"0592║$m_bttp_15_t" = "The Crystarium - Part 2{End}{Question}";
"0593║$m_bttp_16_p0" = "During the course of battle, the status of enemies and allies can be altered in various ways, some beneficial and some detrimental.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}{Color WhitePurple}Synergist{Color SkyBlue} abilities grant status-enhancing effects that strengthen or protect the recipient. {Color WhiteGray}Saboteur{Color SkyBlue} abilities, on the other hand, inflict troublesome {Color Gold}status ailments{Color SkyBlue}. Some enemy attacks can also result in these disadvantageous conditions.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}It is possible for up to 8 status effects to stack simultaneously. Ignore the harmful ones, and you may soon find your fighting capabilities severely limited.{End}{Question}";
"0594║$m_bttp_16_p1" = "Common status effects include bonuses and penalties to offensive and defensive attributes. These can result from using abilities or even equipping certain pieces of gear.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Changes to {Color Gold}Strength{Color SkyBlue} and {Color Gold}Magic{Color SkyBlue} primarily affect the damage characters deal to enemies, with Strength affecting physical attacks and Magic affecting spells. Strength can be boosted with the {Color Gold}Bravery{Color SkyBlue} ability, while the {Color Gold}Faith{Color SkyBlue} ability enhances Magic.{Text NewLine}{Text 112}Changes to resistances affect the amount of damage characters take from enemy attacks. Physical resistance can be improved via the {Color Gold}Protect{Color SkyBlue} ability, or eroded with {Color Gold}Deprotect{Color SkyBlue}. Likewise, magic resistance can be fortified with {Color Gold}Shell{Color SkyBlue} or hampered by {Color Gold}Deshell{Color SkyBlue}.{End}{Question}";
"0595║$m_bttp_16_t" = "Status Effects{End}{Question}";
"0596║$m_bttp_17_p0" = "Some enemies are exceptionally vulnerable to certain {Color Gold}elements{Color SkyBlue}. Attacks that deal damage of the proper type are especially devastating to these opponents.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}By using the {Color Gold}Libra{Color SkyBlue} technique, you can reveal an enemy's resistances to the six elements (earth, fire, ice, lightning, water, and wind) as well as to physical and magic damage.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}The {Color Purple}Ravager{Color SkyBlue} role is particularly skilled at elemental attacks, using spells like {Color Gold}Fire{Color SkyBlue} and {Color Gold}Blizzard{Color SkyBlue} to deal fire and ice damage respectively.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}In addition to spells, some physical attacks like {Color Gold}Sparkstrike{Color SkyBlue} deal elemental damage (in this case, lightning), while the technique {Color Gold}Quake{Color SkyBlue} inflicts earth damage.{End}{Question}";
"0597║$m_bttp_17_p1" = "{Text NewLine}A character need not be a Ravager to deal elemental damage. Affinity-granting abilities like {Color Gold}Enfire{Color SkyBlue} cause normal physical attacks to deal damage of the corresponding element. An icon of a sword combined with the imbued element indicates this status.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Enhancements like {Color Gold}Barfire{Color SkyBlue} minimize the damage from enemies who employ similar attacks and magic, providing bonuses to elemental resistance. These effects are represented by an icon of a shield combined with the resisted element.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}There are no abilities that grant resistance to, or cause attacks to deal, earth or wind damage. However, there are accessories that do so when equipped.{End}{Question}";
"0598║$m_bttp_17_p2" = "Physical and magic resistance always take priority over elemental vulnerabilities.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}For example, if you attack an enemy who is weak against lightning{Var85 87}but immune to magic{Var85 87}with the {Color Gold}Thunder{Color SkyBlue} spell, it will deal no damage. However, attacking the same enemy with {Color Gold}Sparkstrike{Color SkyBlue}{Var85 87}a non-magical lightning attack{Var85 87}will be highly effective.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Some enemies are immune to both physical and magic damage. If you should happen to encounter such fearsome foes, use {Color Gold}Libra{Color SkyBlue} to glean information that might help you overcome them.{End}{Question}";
"0599║$m_bttp_17_t" = "Elemental Damage and Resistance{End}{Question}";
"0600║$m_bttp_18_p0" = "The debuffing and debilitating status ailments inflicted by some abilities render enemies weak and vulnerable. However, opponents can and will use those very same abilities against you. If you do not take steps to counteract them, you may find yourself fighting at a disadvantage.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Some accessories grant resistance to status ailments, as does the {Color Gold}Veil{Color SkyBlue} spell. An icon with an upwards arrow ({Var81 170}) represents an active resistance bonus. (Z){Text NewLine}{Text 112}Icons with a downwards arrow ({Var81 171}) represent detrimental status effects.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}(A) {Color Gold}Debrave{Color SkyBlue}: Reduces Strength.{Text NewLine}(B) {Color Gold}Defaith{Color SkyBlue}: Reduces Magic.{Text NewLine}(C) {Color Gold}Deprotect{Color SkyBlue}: Reduces physical resistance.{Text NewLine}(D) {Color Gold}Deshell{Color SkyBlue}: Reduces magic resistance.{Text NewLine}(E) {Color Gold}Slow{Color SkyBlue}: Reduces ATB gauge rate.{Text NewLine}(F) {Color Gold}Imperil{Color SkyBlue}: Reduces elemental resistance.{Text NewLine}{End}{Question}";
"0601║$m_bttp_18_p1" = "Items remove some status ailments:{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}(A) {Color Gold}Poison{Color SkyBlue}: Deals damage repeatedly over time. Removed by {Color Green}Antidote{Color SkyBlue}.{Text NewLine}(B) {Color Gold}Pain{Color SkyBlue}: Prevents use of physical abilities. Removed by {Color Green}Painkiller{Color SkyBlue}.{Text NewLine}(C) {Color Gold}Fog{Color SkyBlue}: Prevents spell casting. Removed by {Color Green}Mallet{Color SkyBlue}.{Text NewLine}(D) {Color Gold}Daze{Color SkyBlue}: Prevents all actions and increases damage. Removed by {Color Green}Foul Liquid{Color SkyBlue}.{Text NewLine}(E) {Color Gold}Curse{Color SkyBlue}: Causes own abilities to fail often, while rendering opponents' likely to succeed. Removed by {Color Green}Holy Water{Color SkyBlue}.{Text NewLine}{Text 112}The {Color Gold}Esuna{Color SkyBlue} spell can also remove status ailments. This ability removes only the most recently inflicted ailment, so it must be used repeatedly if a character is suffering from more than one.{End}{Question}";
"0602║$m_bttp_18_p2" = "There are also a small number of special status alterations, such as the following:{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}(A) {Color Gold}Doom{Color SkyBlue}: When a character is inflicted with this status, a countdown begins. When the count reaches zero, the character is KO'd. There is no way to stop the effects of {Color Gold}Doom{Color SkyBlue}, but certain accessories grant resistance to the instant KO caused by {Color Gold}Death{Color SkyBlue} and similar abilities.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}(B) {Color Gold}Dispel{Color SkyBlue}: Removes the most recent status enhancement from the target.{End}{Question}";
"0603║$m_bttp_18_t" = "Status Ailments{End}{Question}";
"0604║$m_bttp_19_p0" = "Status effects can be neutralized by applying the opposite effect, which effectively cancels out both. This enables a Synergist to remove status ailments in place of a Medic, and also allows a Saboteur to remove status enhancements from enemies.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}(A) {Color Gold}Debrave{Color SkyBlue} cancels {Color Gold}Bravery{Color SkyBlue}.{Text NewLine}(B) {Color Gold}Defaith{Color SkyBlue} cancels {Color Gold}Faith{Color SkyBlue}.{Text NewLine}(C) {Color Gold}Deprotect{Color SkyBlue} cancels {Color Gold}Protect{Color SkyBlue}.{Text NewLine}(D) {Color Gold}Deshell{Color SkyBlue} cancels {Color Gold}Shell{Color SkyBlue}.{Text NewLine}(E) {Color Gold}Slow{Color SkyBlue} cancels {Color Gold}Haste{Color SkyBlue}.{Text NewLine}(F) {Color Gold}Curse{Color SkyBlue} cancels {Color Gold}Vigilance{Color SkyBlue}.{Text NewLine}(G) {Color Gold}Imperil{Color SkyBlue} cannot be canceled.{End}{Question}";
"0605║$m_bttp_19_t" = "Neutralizing Status Effects{End}{Question}";
"0606║$m_bttp_20_p0" = "The animated scenes played during the summoning of Eidolons can be skipped at any time by pressing {Key Select}, as can the scenes shown upon activating gestalt mode.{End}{Question}";
"0607║$m_bttp_20_t" = "Skipping Summoning Sequences{End}{Question}";
"0608║$m_bttp_21_p0" = "Now that all roles have been unlocked, you can assign roles freely to your characters. However, a character must have learned at least one ability for a role before he or she can don it.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}If you wish to cast a character in a new role, first access the Crystarium and teach that character an ability for the desired role.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Master enough roles, and your choice of paradigms will expand significantly.{End}{Question}";
"0609║$m_bttp_21_t" = "The Crystarium - Part 3{End}{Question}";
"0610║$m_fltp_ajp_p0" = "In many cases, you can jump over obstacles or terrain level differences that appear to impede your progress. To do so, simply approach the obstruction and attempt to continue moving in the direction you wish to proceed. If it is possible to jump over the hurdle, you will do so automatically.{End}{Question}";
"0611║$m_fltp_ajp_t" = "Auto-jump{End}{Question}";
"0612║$m_fltp_atk_p0" = "Upon approaching the other characters you encounter while exploring, you will often be spoken to, or overhear something being said. These conversations occur automatically and do not require any action on your part.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}A few conversations require a button press to initiate. In these instances, a button prompt will be displayed when you approach the person in question, just as a prompt appears when you approach any object on which you can perform an action.{End}{Question}";
"0613║$m_fltp_atk_t" = "Auto-talk{End}{Question}";
"0614║$m_fltp_cms_p0" = "A total of four camera control schemes are available for selection. The control scheme can be changed even after an initial choice is made.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}To modify your current setting, press {Key Triangle} to open the main menu and then select {Color Gold}Settings{Color SkyBlue}.{End}{Question}";
"0615║$m_fltp_cms_t" = "Camera Settings{End}{Question}";
"0616║$m_fltp_evs_p0" = "You can press {Key Start} at any time during a cutscene to pause the action. After doing so, pressing {Key Select} will allow you to skip the rest of the scene if you so desire.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Certain cutscenes are unskippable. If the {Color Gold}Skip{Color SkyBlue} option is not displayed upon pausing, the scene must be viewed in its entirety.{End}{Question}";
"0617║$m_fltp_evs_t" = "Skippable Cutscenes{End}{Question}";
"0618║$m_fltp_kss_p0" = "{Key 92}  Move character{Text NewLine}{Key 93}  Rotate camera{Text NewLine}{Key RSPress}  Reset camera position{Text NewLine}{Key Triangle}   Open main menu{Text NewLine}{Key Cross}   Perform action{Text NewLine}{Key Start} Pause game{End}{Question}";
"0619║$m_fltp_kss_t" = "Basic Controls{End}{Question}";
"0620║$m_fltp_mk2_p0" = "You will find swirling yellow indicators on the ground in the Archylte Steppe that appear in no other locations on Gran Pulse or Cocoon.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}These marks indicate {Color Gold}jump points{Color SkyBlue}, where a creature with enough leg strength just might be able to leap to a distant destination.{End}{Question}";
"0621║$m_fltp_mk2_t" = "Yellow Indicators{End}{Question}";
"0622║$m_fltp_mk_p0" = "Swirling blue and red indicators often mark the ground of the areas you explore.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}{Color BlizzardBlue}Blue{Color SkyBlue} indicators represent points on the ground where it is possible to jump over an{Text NewLine}obstacle. {Color Red}Red{Color SkyBlue} indicators, on the other hand, indicate points you must reach in order{Text NewLine}to operate a device or cause something important to happen.{End}{Question}";
"0623║$m_fltp_mk_t" = "Blue and Red Indicators{End}{Question}";
"0624║$m_fltp_nav_p0" = "The mini-map in the upper right corner of{Text NewLine}the screen displays a variety of helpful information. In addition to revealing the surrounding terrain, the mini-map indicates the direction of your destination and the positions of nearby enemies.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Upon entering an area guarded by hostiles, the mini-map will flash in warning. It also shows where recently defeated enemies had been located, allowing you to quickly reorient yourself after battle.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}You can turn off the mini-map at any time.{Text NewLine}To toggle its display, simply press {Key Select}.{End}{Question}";
"0625║$m_fltp_nav_t" = "The Mini-map{End}{Question}";
"0626║$m_fltp_opt_p0" = "The {Color Gold}paradigm deck{Color SkyBlue} is the list of paradigms available to your party in battle. To modify it, press {Key Triangle} to open the main menu and then select {Color Gold}Paradigms{Color SkyBlue}. Via the menu that appears, you can change the party's active paradigm and also modify its deck.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}To do the latter, choose {Color Gold}Customize{Color SkyBlue}. Select any of the 6 available slots, and you will have the option to edit the paradigm contained therein. You can also reorder the list to suit your preferences using {Key 95} and {Key Cross}. To change the party's active paradigm, select the desired one and press {Key Square}.{End}{Question}";
"0627║$m_fltp_opt_p1" = "If you are not sure how to compose an effective deck, you can also choose {Color Gold}Generate{Color SkyBlue} to create paradigms automatically.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Different paradigms will be generated each time, even if you select the same category. If you do not wish to use the one created first, try generating new paradigms of the same type until you discover one you like.{End}{Question}";
"0628║$m_fltp_opt_t" = "The Paradigm Deck{End}{Question}";
"0629║$m_fltp_shp_p0" = "When you wish to purchase new items or sell items in your party inventory, you will first need to access a {Color Gold}Save Station{Color SkyBlue}.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Approach any Save Station and press {Key Cross} when the word {Color Gold}ACCESS{Color SkyBlue} appears to open the Save Station menu. Select {Color Gold}Shop{Color SkyBlue} from this menu, and then choose the retailer whose network you would like to access.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Your selection will be limited at first, but as you obtain e-passes for new retail networks, you will gain access to a wider variety of vendors and merchandise.{End}{Question}";
"0630║$m_fltp_shp_p1" = "You can obtain the gil needed to make new purchases from treasure spheres, or by selling items that you no longer need.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Shops frequently expand their stocks, offering you the chance to acquire new items. Whenever new merchandise becomes available through a retailer to which you have access, a notice will appear in the upper left corner of the screen. An icon ({Icon Exclamation}) will also appear next to the name of any shop with updated offerings when you choose {Color Gold}Shop{Color SkyBlue} from the Save Station menu.{End}{Question}";
"0631║$m_fltp_shp_t" = "Shopping{End}{Question}";
"0632║$m_fltp_sv_p0" = "As you explore your environs, you will sometimes encounter Save Stations at which you can save your progress.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}To access a Save Station, approach it and press {Key Cross} when the word {Color Gold}ACCESS{Color SkyBlue} appears. A menu of its functions will then appear.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Select {Color Gold}Save{Color SkyBlue} from the menu, and then choose a file to which to save your data. Press {Key Cross} to save your progress to that file.{End}{Question}";
"0633║$m_fltp_sv_t" = "Saving{End}{Question}";
"0634║$m_fltp_tag2_p0" = "You will sometimes find yourself unable to interact with treasure spheres or other devices even when standing directly in front of them. This is due to the presence of enemies in close proximity to the object in question.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}When this occurs, the action button icon does not appear beside the name of the action you would otherwise be able to perform. Defeat the nearby enemies, and you will be able to interact with the object normally.{End}{Question}";
"0635║$m_fltp_tag2_t" = "Object Interaction - Part 2{End}{Question}";
"0636║$m_fltp_tag_p0" = "When you approach an unopened treasure sphere, switch, or any other object on which{Text NewLine}you may perform an action, a message indicating the action will appear.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}Press {Key Cross} to perform this action, obtaining gil or items in the case of a treasure sphere, or activating a device in the case of a switch or control panel.{End}{Question}";
"0637║$m_fltp_tag_t" = "Object Interaction - Part 1{End}{Question}";
"0638║$m_fltp_wmp_p0" = "Area maps display your current position and destination as well as other points of interest in the vicinity.{Text NewLine}{Text NewLine}To open the map of your current location, press {Key Square}. You can also view the map by pressing {Key Triangle} to open the main menu and then selecting {Color Gold}Map{Color SkyBlue}.{End}{Question}";
"0639║$m_fltp_wmp_t" = "Area Maps{End}{Question}";
